[ Screams ]

57
00:04:17,933 --> 00:04:21,899
[ Jack Bauer ]
The following takes place
between 3:00 p.m. and 5:00 p.m.

58
00:04:24,166 --> 00:04:26,100
Events occur in real time.

59
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:41,066
- I thought I told you to
turn up the air-conditioner.
- All right, sir. I do so.

60
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:49,500
[ Lowing ]

61
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,700
- For crying out loud.
- [ Horn Honking ]

62
00:04:55,766 --> 00:04:59,000
- [ Lowing ]
- Go on! Go around them! Go on.

63
00:05:08,267 --> 00:05:10,734
But we need
another player.
Find somebody else.

64
00:05:10,799 --> 00:05:13,833
Who? Tell me, Willie--
Who can handle the ball
better than you?

65
00:05:13,899 --> 00:05:15,866
That's right. No one.

66
00:05:15,933 --> 00:05:18,533
We're not supposed to go
to town without Mr. Benton.

67
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:22,300
Mr. Benton worries too much,
and so do you.
Hey, Desmond!

68
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:24,799
Hurry, or the bus
will leave. Come on.
Let's go.

69
00:05:24,866 --> 00:05:27,899
You're not my father.
I'm your brother,
and you'll do what I say.

70
00:05:27,966 --> 00:05:31,233
- No!
- Fine then.

71
00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:42,100
The truck is here!
The truck is here!

72
00:05:42,166 --> 00:05:44,600
Hey! The truck is here!

73
00:05:45,734 --> 00:05:49,300
[ Speaking Native Language ]
The truck is here!

74
00:05:59,033 --> 00:06:01,166
[ Cheering ]

75
00:06:04,866 --> 00:06:06,899
[ Children Chattering ]

76
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:55,133
I wasn't stealing it.
I swear.

77
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:57,233
I was just looking.

78
00:07:06,033 --> 00:07:07,966
Forgot these.

79
00:07:08,966 --> 00:07:11,066
Very pretty.
For a woman, yes?

80
00:07:12,166 --> 00:07:14,899
I was gonna give it
to my daughter one day.

81
00:07:14,966 --> 00:07:17,966
You have a daughter?
Yeah.

82
00:07:18,033 --> 00:07:21,766
Where did you get it?
Rajasthan.

83
00:07:23,066 --> 00:07:26,533
India. You ask
a lot of questions.

84
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,866
That's what
Mr. Benton says.

85
00:07:28,933 --> 00:07:30,833
I bet.

86
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:34,300
When were you there?

87
00:07:36,567 --> 00:07:38,899
- Last summer.
- Before you came here?

88
00:07:38,966 --> 00:07:41,833
Yes.
And before that,
where were you?

89
00:07:41,899 --> 00:07:45,033
- Different places.
- When are you going home?

90
00:07:46,866 --> 00:07:48,799
I'm not going home.

91
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:53,899
Listen, I told the other boys
I'd help them unload the truck.

92
00:07:53,966 --> 00:07:56,667
- If you want that,
you can keep it.
- Really?

93
00:07:56,734 --> 00:07:58,567
Really.

94
00:08:00,066 --> 00:08:02,600
Willie.

95
00:08:02,667 --> 00:08:05,833
You're gonna have to give me
my knife back though.

96
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:19,533
Go on.

97
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:23,467
Hey, Willie.
The supply truck's here.

98
00:08:23,533 --> 00:08:25,966
- The boys could use some help.
- Look what Jack gave me.

99
00:08:27,467 --> 00:08:29,533
Very nice.
It's from India.

100
00:08:31,799 --> 00:08:33,734
Jack, this is
Frank Tramell.

101
00:08:33,799 --> 00:08:36,600
He's the ambassador's
chief political officer.

102
00:08:36,667 --> 00:08:38,766
I know who he is.

103
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:42,200
He says he left some
messages for you to come
see him at the embassy.

104
00:08:42,267 --> 00:08:45,533
I got his messages.
What's going on, Jack?

105
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,600
I'll tell you
what's going on.

106
00:08:47,667 --> 00:08:49,766
The senate subcommittee
has questions...

107
00:08:49,833 --> 00:08:54,433
about the illegal detention and
torture of certain prisoners
in Mr. Bauer's custody.

108
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:58,000
I have a subpoena
requesting you to appear,
and it's way past due.

109
00:08:58,066 --> 00:09:00,400
So consider yourself served.
[ Panting ]

110
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:09,267
I told the boys I'd
help them unload the truck.
Excuse me.

111
00:09:11,033 --> 00:09:13,833
Failure to comply to
a subpoena is a federal
offense, Mr. Bauer.

112
00:09:13,899 --> 00:09:17,166
You are bound by law
to respond.
Then give them my response.

113
00:09:17,233 --> 00:09:19,734
They want me
back in Washington,
they can come and get me.

114
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:30,933
The, uh, ambassador
said...

115
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:34,634
that you and Bauer were
in the special forces
together?

116
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:37,400
- How long has he been here?
- A few months.

117
00:09:37,467 --> 00:09:41,533
He never mentioned
the subpoena?
Nope.

118
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:45,133
Well, he's been ducking it
for more than a year, across
three different continents.

119
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:48,166
Washington is leaning
on the ambassador
to deliver him.

120
00:09:48,233 --> 00:09:50,467
And now the ambassador's
leaning on you.

121
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:54,600
Bauer doesn't come back
to the States on his own,
they'll come for him.

122
00:09:54,667 --> 00:09:58,300
That would be a mistake.
You're doing God's work
here, Carl.

123
00:09:58,367 --> 00:10:00,833
Between malaria
and the wars,

124
00:10:00,899 --> 00:10:02,899
these kids never
had a chance.

125
00:10:02,966 --> 00:10:04,899
Now you're giving them
a decent life.

126
00:10:04,966 --> 00:10:07,833
It'd be a shame
if the funding dried up.
Don't threaten me, Frank.

127
00:10:07,899 --> 00:10:10,166
I'm just giving you
the facts.

128
00:10:10,233 --> 00:10:13,766
You're his friend.
Talk some damn sense
into him.

129
00:10:25,267 --> 00:10:26,899
Here, Jack.
Thank you, Thomas.

130
00:10:26,966 --> 00:10:29,467
Okay. Go back.

131
00:10:29,533 --> 00:10:31,533
Now you. Go, go.
There he is.

132
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:37,066
The mighty warrior
who traded his gun
for a wheelbarrow.

133
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:40,000
Why are you here, hmm?

134
00:10:40,066 --> 00:10:42,267
To do penance
for all your sins?

135
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:47,600
You don't want
to talk about it.
I don't blame you.

136
00:10:55,966 --> 00:10:59,233
- Watch out.
- The man from the embassy--
What did he want?

137
00:10:59,300 --> 00:11:02,133
Nothing. He just
wanted to talk.
Talk about what?

138
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:05,233
Willie, you ask
too many damn questions.

139
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:07,300
[ Man ]
Let's go. Here's the oranges.

140
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:15,933
Willie? Come here.
I need your help.

141
00:11:21,567 --> 00:11:25,133
Thank you. Come with me.

142
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:30,333
[ Thomas ]
Jimmy. Take a box.

143
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:33,600
Here. Careful.
Don't drop it.

144
00:11:33,667 --> 00:11:36,166
[ Men Shouting ]

145
00:11:39,533 --> 00:11:42,300
The government won't
be able to hold out
against us for long.

146
00:11:42,367 --> 00:11:46,267
Except we have more weapons
than soldiers who can use them.

147
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:50,066
We need to overrun
the main garrison
from the west.

148
00:11:50,133 --> 00:11:52,700
We have minefields
here and here.

149
00:11:52,766 --> 00:11:56,200
Then I'll bring you more
little soldiers to clear them.
Do not worry.

150
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:04,700
Our father would be
really proud, Youssou.
Very proud.

151
00:12:08,467 --> 00:12:11,066
You will have
your little soldiers.

152
00:12:16,033 --> 00:12:18,000
Go.

153
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:21,000
[ Ringing ]

154
00:12:22,166 --> 00:12:25,899
[ Ringing, Beeps ]

155
00:12:27,233 --> 00:12:30,166
This is Colonel Dubaku.
Hodges here.

156
00:12:30,233 --> 00:12:33,133
I've just heard some
troubling news, Colonel,

157
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:37,500
that your recruiting numbers
are-- are still coming up
a little short.

158
00:12:37,567 --> 00:12:40,133
I want you to know
my offer stands.

159
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:42,367
I've got personnel standing by
right across the border.

160
00:12:42,433 --> 00:12:45,467
They can be deployed
within the hour.
That won't be necessary.

161
00:12:45,533 --> 00:12:47,467
Oh?

162
00:12:47,533 --> 00:12:49,533
Do some thinking now,
Colonel.

163
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:53,400
I'm offering you professional
soldiers, not children you
haven't had time to train.

164
00:12:53,467 --> 00:12:56,966
You provided the weapons.
We will fight our own war.

165
00:12:57,033 --> 00:13:00,033
Well, it's your country.

166
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:02,100
It will be, soon.

167
00:13:03,100 --> 00:13:05,400
Is there anything else,
Mr. Hodges?

168
00:13:05,467 --> 00:13:08,533
Yeah.
Uh, tell General Juma...

169
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:10,933
give me a call
when he gets there,
will you?

170
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,267
I'll let him know.
Good.

171
00:13:13,333 --> 00:13:15,267
[ Beeps ]

172
00:13:23,433 --> 00:13:26,533
That's one hard-nosed
son of a bitch.

173
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:28,333
It is his country.

174
00:13:29,667 --> 00:13:31,667
But I'm paying for it.

175
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:36,833
I don't want
those transactions
traceable,

176
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:39,000
Mr. Nichols.

177
00:13:39,066 --> 00:13:43,467
Not by the S.E.C.,
the I.R.S. or any
of my ex-wives.

178
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:49,367
You understand me,
don't you?

179
00:13:53,467 --> 00:13:55,400
[ Chattering ]

180
00:13:55,467 --> 00:13:58,133
John, what do you want me
to tell you?

181
00:13:58,200 --> 00:14:00,600
You gotta hang in there
and be patient, my friend.
I'm trying.

182
00:14:00,667 --> 00:14:03,133
Yeah, yeah. I know.
Hold on, hold on.
Stop. Stop.

183
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:05,899
We got caught by the margin.
It's gonna turn around.

184
00:14:05,966 --> 00:14:08,899
Yes. Yes, it is.
Yes, it is.

185
00:14:08,966 --> 00:14:11,433
Yeah, you've gotta
give it time...

186
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:14,799
and just, yeah,
be patient.

187
00:14:14,866 --> 00:14:18,133
Yeah. Okay.
Yes. Yes. Okay.

188
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:20,166
All right. Bye-bye.

189
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:24,567
[ Man ]
All right. Next up. Right?

190
00:14:24,634 --> 00:14:26,866
[ Intercom Beeps ]
[ Nichols ]
Chris.

191
00:14:28,467 --> 00:14:30,866
Yeah.
Would you come in here,
please?

192
00:15:02,166 --> 00:15:03,933
Who's that guy?
A client.

193
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:08,400
I need you to close out
Abu Dhabi and Eritrea.

194
00:15:08,467 --> 00:15:10,667
Burn the records
and bury the ashes.

195
00:15:12,766 --> 00:15:15,833
Go.
Yeah.

196
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:21,966
Jack.
Can I have a word?

197
00:15:22,033 --> 00:15:26,500
Yeah. Willie,
go on out to the truck.
Pick up another load.

198
00:15:26,567 --> 00:15:28,567
It's all right.
Go, go.

199
00:15:35,866 --> 00:15:38,033
I think you should
take a look at this.

200
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:41,866
I don't need to.
I know what it says.

201
00:15:43,667 --> 00:15:46,333
Don't worry, Carl.
I'll be gone by dark.

202
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:49,634
I'm not asking you to leave,
Jack. I'm asking you
to have a conversation.

203
00:15:53,367 --> 00:15:56,966
Tramell says
this subpoena's been chasing
you for over a year now.

204
00:15:57,033 --> 00:16:00,200
It's gonna catch up
with you sometime.
I'm not going back.

205
00:16:01,333 --> 00:16:03,333
I'm not saying you should.

206
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:06,533
But a year's a long time
to spend looking
over your shoulder.

207
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:09,000
A lifetime of that's
gonna drive you
out of your mind.

208
00:16:09,066 --> 00:16:11,233
Whatever I've done
I've paid for in full.

209
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:14,833
All I've got left
is my freedom. I'm not lettin'
them take that away from me.

210
00:16:14,899 --> 00:16:17,899
Freedom. What kind
of freedom's this, Jack?
You're runnin' away.

211
00:16:17,966 --> 00:16:20,899
What do you want
from me, Carl?
What do you want?

212
00:16:23,300 --> 00:16:25,700
I want you to trust me, Jack.
I am your friend.

213
00:16:27,533 --> 00:16:30,866
I'm sorry.
Look.

214
00:16:30,933 --> 00:16:34,200
I can't remember
the many times
you saved my life.

215
00:16:34,267 --> 00:16:36,567
But I do know
that I owe you.

216
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,567
You've lost a lot, Jack.

217
00:16:42,634 --> 00:16:45,100
I know that.
I know that.

218
00:16:45,166 --> 00:16:50,100
When you called me up
for the first time in--
What? Ten years?

219
00:16:50,166 --> 00:16:54,166
I hoped you were maybe
looking for more than
just a place to stay.

220
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:58,200
I'm trying to
find a way to make
some sense of it all.

221
00:16:58,267 --> 00:17:00,966
It's a normal impulse,
especially for people
like us.

222
00:17:01,033 --> 00:17:04,100
Yeah, except you found
what you were looking for.

223
00:17:06,734 --> 00:17:08,667
Yeah.

224
00:17:08,734 --> 00:17:10,866
[ Hammering ]

225
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:15,066
Damn it.

226
00:17:15,133 --> 00:17:17,667
Carl.

227
00:17:17,734 --> 00:17:19,667
Carl!

228
00:17:20,966 --> 00:17:23,300
I just meant
it's different for me.

229
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:30,166
You never asked me
why I quit.

230
00:17:32,667 --> 00:17:36,033
I figured
you would have told me
if you wanted me to know.

231
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:53,500
While I was in Beirut--

232
00:17:54,634 --> 00:17:57,799
a counterinsurgency
operation.

233
00:18:00,267 --> 00:18:03,267
I was holding a suspect.

234
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:06,333
The attack window was open.
Our time was limited.

235
00:18:08,634 --> 00:18:12,133
I was sure I had the right guy,
but he wasn't giving me
the information I needed,

236
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:14,166
so I kept pushing.

237
00:18:16,766 --> 00:18:19,899
Pushed him hard...

238
00:18:19,966 --> 00:18:23,400
until he finally told me
what I wanted to hear...

239
00:18:23,467 --> 00:18:25,400
right before he died.

240
00:18:29,433 --> 00:18:31,766
He wasn't the right guy, Jack.

241
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:37,467
The intel was bad.

242
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:41,166
- I lost 14 men
and 21 civilians that day.
- Carl, that's the job.

243
00:18:41,233 --> 00:18:43,500
People like you and me, Jack--
We don't--

244
00:18:44,933 --> 00:18:48,267
We don't keep score
by counting how many lives
we've saved,

245
00:18:49,634 --> 00:18:51,899
but by how many we've lost.

246
00:18:56,933 --> 00:19:00,433
You know, I'm not so sure
I have found what
I was lookin' for.

247
00:19:01,799 --> 00:19:04,300
But I have found a way
to live with myself.

248
00:19:07,533 --> 00:19:09,467
It took a long time.

249
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:14,799
The first thing I had to do
was stop running.

250
00:19:18,467 --> 00:19:20,467
I meant what I said, Jack.

251
00:19:21,734 --> 00:19:24,866
You can stay here.
We'll fight this thing
together.

252
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:29,467
Sorry.

253
00:19:29,533 --> 00:19:31,933
Don't worry about Tramell.

254
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:34,233
The state department's
not the only place
with money.

255
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:37,933
I appreciate what
you're trying to do, Carl,
but this is my problem.

256
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:41,433
I'm not gonna
let it become yours.

257
00:19:43,066 --> 00:19:45,799
Remember what the lieutenant
used to say about trouble?

258
00:19:45,866 --> 00:19:47,866
"Comes cheap,
leaves expensive."

259
00:19:47,933 --> 00:19:49,899
Yeah. Yeah.

260
00:19:53,667 --> 00:19:55,833
What you've done
with this place.

261
00:19:57,367 --> 00:20:00,200
The school, what you've
done for the boys--
It's worth protecting.

262
00:20:02,133 --> 00:20:06,200
You and I both know
it'd be better for everyone
if I leave.

263
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:18,634
I'm sorry, Jack.
Me too.

264
00:20:18,700 --> 00:20:21,700
[ Chuckling ]
Me too.

265
00:20:25,866 --> 00:20:29,300
Thank you, Carl.
I mean that.

266
00:20:29,367 --> 00:20:31,367
Thank you for everything.

267
00:20:31,433 --> 00:20:33,500
Always.

268
00:20:33,567 --> 00:20:35,467
Yeah.

269
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:54,734
- Where is he going?
- I'm not sure.

270
00:20:55,766 --> 00:20:57,567
But he's leaving.

271
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:00,166
Yeah.

272
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,000
He is.

273
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:11,267
You are just a boy.
You do not know what you
are talking about.

274
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:14,433
What do you know?
This isn't even
your country, yeah?

275
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:18,433
- Hey, hey, hey!
What's goin' on?
- Thomas is talking nonsense.

276
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:22,467
He's spreading rumors
about Juma.
Rumors? They are not rumors.

277
00:21:22,533 --> 00:21:25,866
Juma's soldiers have
been crossing the border
and stealing our children.

278
00:21:25,933 --> 00:21:30,033
Juma has no soldiers,
and he has no weapons.
Everyone knows that.

279
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:34,799
My cousin is missing.
He went to the market yesterday,
and he has not returned.

280
00:21:34,866 --> 00:21:38,600
Then it was gunrunners
that took him, or someone
from the diamond mines.

281
00:21:38,667 --> 00:21:41,066
My brother is in town
with James.

282
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:44,300
You see that, hmm?
Now you have the boy worried.

283
00:21:44,367 --> 00:21:47,333
He should be worried.
We should all be worried.

284
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:49,166
Stop it, both of you.

285
00:21:49,233 --> 00:21:52,933
Finish up work.
I'll go into town and see if we
can find out what's going on.

286
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,500
- Fine, but you are
wasting your time.
- [ Thomas ] Take this.

287
00:21:55,567 --> 00:21:58,433
I thought I told you kids
not to go into town
without telling me.

288
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:01,033
Desmond never listens
to anyone but Desmond.

289
00:22:01,100 --> 00:22:03,766
Where'd he go?
Playing football.

290
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:06,833
There's a field
just past the bridge.

291
00:22:06,899 --> 00:22:10,166
I'll be back soon.
Benton.

292
00:22:10,233 --> 00:22:13,033
You're not seriously worried
about all of this, are you?

293
00:22:13,100 --> 00:22:16,233
If Juma was making trouble,
we would have heard something,
no?

294
00:22:16,300 --> 00:22:19,966
Probably,
but this is Sangala.
I'm not taking any chances.

295
00:22:20,033 --> 00:22:22,734
[ Children Laughing ]

296
00:22:26,667 --> 00:22:29,766
[ Thomas Chattering ]

297
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:31,866
[ Excited Shouting ]

298
00:22:37,766 --> 00:22:40,533
Yo. Hey.
Pass it! Pass it!

299
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:47,166
[ Bleating ]

300
00:23:00,734 --> 00:23:05,267
Left, left, left!
Pass the ball, James.
The ball!

301
00:23:05,333 --> 00:23:07,300
What'd you think
that was, huh?
Nothing.

302
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:09,500
What you say, "nothing"?
Now you wanna fight.

303
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:13,634
Oh, wow!
He's so powerful, guys.
Give him a hand.

304
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:17,033
Oh, you just threw
the ball away.
Now you wanna fight.

305
00:23:17,100 --> 00:23:19,033
Now you wanna fight.
Yes.

306
00:23:19,100 --> 00:23:21,766
Go fetch the ball
if you want the ball.
Go fetch it.

307
00:23:27,766 --> 00:23:30,400
- Run!
- [ Machine Gun Fire ]

308
00:23:30,467 --> 00:23:33,066
[ Boys Screaming ]

309
00:23:34,700 --> 00:23:38,066
[ Machine Gun Fire Continues ]

310
00:23:40,734 --> 00:23:43,467
Oh, no!

311
00:23:51,933 --> 00:23:53,667
[ Men Shouting ]

312
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,866
[ Speaking Native Language ]

313
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:07,567
[ Whistling ]
[ Shouting Continues ]

314
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:14,100
[ Shouting Continues ]

315
00:24:18,667 --> 00:24:20,567
Yeah. Yeah.

316
00:24:20,634 --> 00:24:23,400
One at a time.
One at a time.
One at a time!

317
00:24:36,933 --> 00:24:40,500
You are now soldiers
in the People's Freedom Army.

318
00:24:41,966 --> 00:24:45,267
You will all have the honor
of fighting the imperialists...

319
00:24:45,333 --> 00:24:48,233
until we have
taken back our land.

320
00:24:49,300 --> 00:24:51,367
[ Radio Chatter ]

321
00:24:51,433 --> 00:24:55,933
Samuel tells me you are
from the American school
in Okavango.

322
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:58,600
These Americans
make our people slaves.

323
00:24:58,667 --> 00:25:00,700
But we will free you,

324
00:25:00,766 --> 00:25:03,033
and we will free
the other children...

325
00:25:03,100 --> 00:25:06,200
so they can become soldiers.

326
00:25:06,267 --> 00:25:09,000
Take them.
Let's go.

327
00:25:09,066 --> 00:25:11,700
Come on. Go, go!

328
00:25:11,766 --> 00:25:14,799
[ Laughing ]

329
00:25:21,066 --> 00:25:22,799
Tell me your name.

330
00:25:23,866 --> 00:25:25,799
Seville.
Louder.

331
00:25:25,866 --> 00:25:28,766
Seville.
Are you a baby, Seville?

332
00:25:30,467 --> 00:25:34,333
I asked you a question.
Are you a baby?

333
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:38,966
No.
Good, because we need
soldiers, Seville.

334
00:25:39,033 --> 00:25:41,833
Not babies
who wet themselves.

335
00:25:41,899 --> 00:25:44,799
Now stop crying,
or I'll stop you myself.

336
00:25:44,866 --> 00:25:46,899
[ Man ]
Commander!

337
00:25:46,966 --> 00:25:50,367
Put them in the truck!
Let's go!

338
00:25:52,133 --> 00:25:54,233
Go. Go!

339
00:25:58,367 --> 00:26:00,100
Faster! Don't lose them!

340
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:08,333
- [ Gasping ]
- What are you doing?

341
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:12,634
Idiot! They are
no good to us dead!

342
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:14,667
Go!

343
00:26:24,700 --> 00:26:27,567
This is an historic day
marking the swearing in...

344
00:26:27,634 --> 00:26:29,799
of America's first
female president.

345
00:26:29,866 --> 00:26:34,333
Behind me, the sidewalks
along Pennsylvania Avenue
are crowded with spectators...

346
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:36,700
here to catch a glimpse
of the passing motorcade.

347
00:26:36,766 --> 00:26:39,933
With the inauguration
less than two hours away,

348
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:43,833
President Daniels is scheduled
to meet with his successor
here at the White House...

349
00:26:43,899 --> 00:26:46,899
to review final details
for the transfer of power.

350
00:26:46,966 --> 00:26:50,300
Their respective transition
teams have been working together
for several weeks...

351
00:26:50,367 --> 00:26:52,734
to ensure
a smooth turnover.
[ Chuckling ]

352
00:26:52,799 --> 00:26:54,799
Stop looking at me
like that.

353
00:26:54,866 --> 00:26:58,533
Watching you get dressed
is almost as fun as
watching you get undressed.

354
00:26:58,600 --> 00:27:01,799
Uh-huh.
Shouldn't you
be getting dressed?

355
00:27:01,866 --> 00:27:03,866
We got time.

356
00:27:04,866 --> 00:27:06,799
Mmm.

357
00:27:08,899 --> 00:27:11,300
Hey, you need to shave.
You're gonna be on TV.

358
00:27:11,367 --> 00:27:13,734
Mmm, mmm.
Stop it.

359
00:27:13,799 --> 00:27:16,600
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]

360
00:27:20,500 --> 00:27:22,433
[ Beeps ]
Hello.

361
00:27:22,500 --> 00:27:24,233
Uh, I need to talk
to you, Rog.

362
00:27:24,300 --> 00:27:26,667
Chris?
Yeah. Look.

363
00:27:26,734 --> 00:27:30,899
Uh, I think I might
be in trouble.
Okay.

364
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:34,933
You using again?
That's not what
this is about.

365
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:37,166
You didn't answer
my question.

366
00:27:37,233 --> 00:27:40,233
I can't, uh--
I can't really talk
on the phone, okay?

367
00:27:40,300 --> 00:27:44,000
I was hoping that I could,
um-- I could meet up with you
face to face.

368
00:27:44,066 --> 00:27:46,799
- Now?
- Rog, hang on a second.

369
00:27:49,966 --> 00:27:53,166
Chris?
I know. I know, I know.
It's terrible timing.

370
00:27:53,233 --> 00:27:57,667
Believe me, I know.
But I wouldn't be asking if
it wasn't really important.

371
00:27:57,734 --> 00:28:02,066
- I gotta leave
in 45 minutes, man.
- I can be there in 20.

372
00:28:02,133 --> 00:28:05,567
Chris--
I am not gonna stay long.
I swear, Rog. Just please.

373
00:28:05,634 --> 00:28:07,667
Do this for me?

374
00:28:10,966 --> 00:28:15,367
- Fine, but I'm outta here
in 45 minutes.
- Thank you. Thank you.

375
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:21,700
You're letting Chris
come here right now?

376
00:28:21,766 --> 00:28:24,166
He's having some kind
of relapse or something.
What am I supposed to do?

377
00:28:24,233 --> 00:28:26,667
Exactly! What are you
supposed to do?

378
00:28:26,734 --> 00:28:30,833
- Make sure he calls
his sponsor? I don't know.
- This is so Chris.

379
00:28:30,899 --> 00:28:32,899
He's been a friend
for a really long time.

380
00:28:32,966 --> 00:28:37,000
He got me my job,
which, if he hadn't,
I wouldn't have met you.

381
00:28:37,066 --> 00:28:39,833
Don't. Stop.
Hmm? Hmm?

382
00:28:42,667 --> 00:28:45,033
[ Sighs ]

383
00:28:46,799 --> 00:28:50,166
Just don't be late
for your mother's
inauguration.

384
00:28:50,233 --> 00:28:52,166
Okay?

385
00:28:52,233 --> 00:28:55,300
[ Man ]
I always liked
his advice too.

386
00:28:55,367 --> 00:28:58,333
Madam President?
Not yet.

387
00:28:58,400 --> 00:29:00,367
This way.

388
00:29:04,966 --> 00:29:07,033
Nice to see you.
Hello.

389
00:29:10,333 --> 00:29:13,567
[ Sighs ]
How are you feeling?

390
00:29:13,634 --> 00:29:15,600
Excited.

391
00:29:16,933 --> 00:29:19,066
Nervous.
You should be.

392
00:29:19,133 --> 00:29:22,500
In a few hours,
you're going to be the most
powerful person in the world.

393
00:29:22,567 --> 00:29:25,267
As if you're not already
hard enough to live with.

394
00:29:25,333 --> 00:29:27,333
Ma'am. Mr. Taylor.
Tom.

395
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:31,100
The president apologizes
he could not be here
to greet you in person.

396
00:29:31,166 --> 00:29:33,267
But something urgent
has come up.
Something urgent?

397
00:29:36,600 --> 00:29:39,966
Whatever it is, Tom,
it's gonna land on my desk
in about two hours.

398
00:29:40,033 --> 00:29:42,533
Could I just
have a moment?

399
00:29:43,533 --> 00:29:46,166
I'm sorry.
Don't be. Go ahead.

400
00:29:48,233 --> 00:29:51,667
Our embassy in Sangala
just got word
of an imminent coup.

401
00:29:51,734 --> 00:29:54,200
How imminent?
Very.

402
00:29:54,267 --> 00:29:57,667
Where's the president now?
He's in
the TelePresence suite.

403
00:29:57,734 --> 00:30:01,467
He's on a secure line
with Prime Minister Matobo.

404
00:30:01,533 --> 00:30:04,367
Mr. President,
my country's in crisis,
and here is the proof.

405
00:30:06,433 --> 00:30:08,766
[ Beeps ]

406
00:30:08,833 --> 00:30:11,066
This video
was taken moments ago.

407
00:30:11,133 --> 00:30:13,833
Juma's moving his forces
toward the capital as we speak.

408
00:30:15,567 --> 00:30:19,200
Mr. Prime Minister,
this news has caught us
all by surprise.

409
00:30:19,267 --> 00:30:24,033
But our priority here
in Washington is to ensure the
safety of you and your family.

410
00:30:24,100 --> 00:30:27,899
My priority
is to defend my country
from this monster Juma,

411
00:30:27,966 --> 00:30:30,533
and the only way
that can happen
is if you accelerate...

412
00:30:30,600 --> 00:30:33,766
the military assistance
your congress has already
pledged to us.

413
00:30:33,833 --> 00:30:37,233
Unfortunately,
I'm not in a position
to make that happen.

414
00:30:38,966 --> 00:30:42,033
Certainly not today.
What about
your successor?

415
00:30:42,100 --> 00:30:44,966
Will she be
in a better position
to help us?

416
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:48,333
I'm afraid I can't
speak for her.

417
00:30:49,667 --> 00:30:52,700
- Will you excuse us
for a moment?
- Yes, of course.

418
00:30:54,233 --> 00:30:56,933
[ Beeps ]
You were right, sir.

419
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:59,966
Taylor does want to
weigh in on this.

420
00:31:01,333 --> 00:31:02,933
Where is she?
Just outside.

421
00:31:05,667 --> 00:31:09,300
- [ Beeps ]
- I am sorry,
Mr. Prime Minister,

422
00:31:09,367 --> 00:31:11,367
but I have to
cut this short.

423
00:31:11,433 --> 00:31:14,100
The president-elect
is waiting for me.

424
00:31:14,166 --> 00:31:17,766
Please, sir,
convey to her my request
for military assistance.

425
00:31:18,899 --> 00:31:21,799
I'll do that.
Thank you, sir.

426
00:31:22,799 --> 00:31:25,166
[ Beeps ]

427
00:31:28,066 --> 00:31:30,000
Well, my first day.

428
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:38,166
Mr. President.
Senator Taylor.

429
00:31:56,300 --> 00:32:00,033
Tom told me
what's happening
in Sangala.

430
00:32:00,100 --> 00:32:03,766
It is a damn tough
situation.
I don't understand.

431
00:32:03,833 --> 00:32:07,133
How could Juma raise an army
without our getting wind of it?

432
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:09,166
We disarmed him
three years ago.

433
00:32:09,233 --> 00:32:13,899
The U.N.'s been
monitoring the situation.
Not closely enough apparently.

434
00:32:13,966 --> 00:32:17,200
Then you have no idea
who's supplying him?

435
00:32:17,267 --> 00:32:21,100
All we know is Juma's
secured some fairly advanced
weapons systems,

436
00:32:21,166 --> 00:32:23,833
which is why
Prime Minister Matobo...

437
00:32:23,899 --> 00:32:27,033
is asking for
our military assistance.

438
00:32:27,100 --> 00:32:29,734
And what did you tell him?
The truth.
It's not a viable option.

439
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:35,667
You don't agree.

440
00:32:35,734 --> 00:32:38,200
We have troops in the region.

441
00:32:38,267 --> 00:32:41,799
A show of force
might make Juma blink.

442
00:32:41,866 --> 00:32:45,133
And if it doesn't,
we get caught up in
another civil quagmire...

443
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:47,267
halfway around the world.

444
00:32:47,333 --> 00:32:49,300
Now, that is
a hard sell.

445
00:32:49,367 --> 00:32:53,100
Especially when there's nothing
in Sangala worth protecting.

446
00:32:53,166 --> 00:32:56,300
No natural resources,
no substantial economic ties,

447
00:32:56,367 --> 00:32:58,700
nothing that threatens
our national security.

448
00:32:59,966 --> 00:33:02,133
The last time Juma
made a power grab,

449
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:07,133
he ignited a tribal war
that killed tens of thousands
of civilians.

450
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:10,866
Our involvement
could avert a genocide.

451
00:33:10,933 --> 00:33:13,600
And this war
will be tragic too.

452
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:18,533
But it isn't our war.

453
00:33:18,600 --> 00:33:23,367
Which is why I've ordered the
ambassador to begin evacuating
all nonmilitary nationals.

454
00:33:25,066 --> 00:33:27,066
I think that's a mistake.

455
00:33:27,133 --> 00:33:30,133
I don't want any Americans
caught in the cross fire
when Juma starts shooting.

456
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:33,433
Closing our embassy
sends a signal to the world...

457
00:33:33,500 --> 00:33:37,200
that we are willing to
sell out a democratic ally...

458
00:33:37,267 --> 00:33:39,267
to a war criminal.

459
00:33:41,734 --> 00:33:43,766
I appreciate
your idealism.

460
00:33:47,567 --> 00:33:51,267
I can't say the same
for your cynicism.

461
00:33:54,166 --> 00:33:58,400
Let's talk after you've
been sitting in my chair
for a while.

462
00:34:01,567 --> 00:34:05,866
And until then, we still
have some transition
business to go over,

463
00:34:05,933 --> 00:34:08,833
so I suggest we get started.

464
00:34:08,899 --> 00:34:10,866
[ Intercom Beeps ]
Send in Tom Lennox.

465
00:34:10,933 --> 00:34:13,166
[ Woman On Intercom ]
Yes, Mr. President.

466
00:34:47,734 --> 00:34:50,267
[ Women Chattering ]

467
00:34:54,333 --> 00:34:57,233
Mademoiselle.
S'il vous plaît.

468
00:34:57,300 --> 00:34:59,333
[ Speaking French ]

469
00:35:00,933 --> 00:35:02,899
[ French Continues ]

470
00:35:05,866 --> 00:35:07,799
Merci, merci.

471
00:35:10,467 --> 00:35:12,433
[ Chattering Resumes ]

472
00:35:37,066 --> 00:35:39,333
[ Gunshots ]

473
00:35:51,799 --> 00:35:53,734
No.

474
00:36:07,799 --> 00:36:09,766
Desmond!

475
00:36:09,833 --> 00:36:12,567
Desmond!

476
00:36:20,634 --> 00:36:22,634
Desmond.

477
00:36:22,700 --> 00:36:25,033
Desmond!

478
00:36:25,100 --> 00:36:28,433
Open your eyes.
Open your eyes!
That's it.

479
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:32,100
Stay with me, Desmond.
Stay with me. Open your eyes.

480
00:36:32,166 --> 00:36:34,667
Open your eyes.
Do not go to sleep.

481
00:36:34,734 --> 00:36:37,500
Do you understand?
Do not go to sleep.

482
00:36:37,567 --> 00:36:39,533
Good lad.

483
00:36:40,567 --> 00:36:42,567
Don't go to sleep.

484
00:36:46,500 --> 00:36:48,500
[ Boy ]
Then you're out.

485
00:36:50,799 --> 00:36:52,833
No.

486
00:36:57,133 --> 00:36:59,033
It's not heavy.

487
00:36:59,100 --> 00:37:01,300
I can carry it.

488
00:37:03,500 --> 00:37:05,433
I want to go
with you.

489
00:37:05,500 --> 00:37:07,734
Me and my brother Desmond too.

490
00:37:07,799 --> 00:37:11,200
- We can carry your things
and work for you.
- No.

491
00:37:11,267 --> 00:37:13,100
Why not?

492
00:37:13,166 --> 00:37:15,533
Because you can't.

493
00:37:18,567 --> 00:37:20,966
I'm going alone.

494
00:37:21,033 --> 00:37:23,933
"People who like
to be alone are witches,"
my grandfather says.

495
00:37:24,000 --> 00:37:26,600
Well, there you go.

496
00:37:26,667 --> 00:37:29,766
Your grandfather wouldn't
be happy if you left here
with a witch, now, would he?

497
00:37:29,833 --> 00:37:31,766
He would want me
to go to America.

498
00:37:31,833 --> 00:37:33,667
His favorite
was Elvis Presley.

499
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:37,766
I'm not going to America.

500
00:37:37,833 --> 00:37:41,333
Where are you going then?
I don't know yet.

501
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:43,799
"I don't know yet"
is better than here.

502
00:37:43,866 --> 00:37:45,799
You sure about that?

503
00:37:45,866 --> 00:37:47,866
Here doesn't seem
so bad to me.

504
00:37:47,933 --> 00:37:52,233
Mr. Benton is very nice,
but there are too many
ghosts walking around.

505
00:37:52,300 --> 00:37:55,933
Ghosts?
My mother, my father
and my three sisters.

506
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:58,634
They live in the bush
and come out at night.

507
00:37:58,700 --> 00:38:01,899
But you wouldn't see them
because you are Poo-mui.
Poo-mui?

508
00:38:01,966 --> 00:38:04,567
A white person.

509
00:38:06,267 --> 00:38:09,033
Willie, you and I
are friends, right?

510
00:38:10,899 --> 00:38:14,100
Then I want you
to do me a favor,
as a friend.

511
00:38:14,166 --> 00:38:17,533
I want you to stay here
with Mr. Benton and help
take care of the other boys.

512
00:38:17,600 --> 00:38:20,567
Can you do that?

513
00:38:20,634 --> 00:38:22,600
You promise?
I promise.

514
00:38:23,734 --> 00:38:25,667
Okay.

515
00:38:42,500 --> 00:38:44,433
Thank you.

516
00:38:53,066 --> 00:38:57,433
It's not fair.
How come he has to go,
and we have to stay?

517
00:38:57,500 --> 00:38:59,634
It's not fair
or unfair.

518
00:38:59,700 --> 00:39:01,833
It's just
the way it is. Come.

519
00:39:01,899 --> 00:39:04,833
Help me finish.
We're almost done.

520
00:39:24,533 --> 00:39:26,500
Jack!

521
00:39:26,567 --> 00:39:29,766
Benton from Direct Connect.
He says he needs to talk to you.

522
00:39:29,833 --> 00:39:34,400
- Carl?
- Jack. James is dead.
Desmond's been shot.

523
00:39:34,467 --> 00:39:36,600
- What happened?
- Juma's raising an army.

524
00:39:36,667 --> 00:39:39,100
Desmond says they're
headed for the school.

525
00:39:39,166 --> 00:39:43,200
They're coming for the boys,
Jack. You got to get them
into the shelter.

526
00:39:43,267 --> 00:39:45,333
Thomas knows where it is.
How many guns are coming?

527
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:48,233
Maybe a dozen. I don't know.
You'll have to hold them off
till I get there.

528
00:39:48,300 --> 00:39:51,333
Carl, you need to call
the embassy, get them to send
some marines out here.

529
00:39:51,400 --> 00:39:54,300
I've been trying.
I can't get through.
Jack, go into my room.

530
00:39:54,367 --> 00:39:58,267
You'll find what you need
in a locker under my sink. The
key's on top of the cupboard.

531
00:39:58,333 --> 00:40:01,799
How far out are you?
Maybe five minutes.

532
00:40:01,866 --> 00:40:05,333
Jack, don't let them
take my kids.

533
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:08,200
- Don't let them
take the children.
- Carl, I won't.

534
00:40:08,267 --> 00:40:12,166
Everybody! Everybody,
I want you to listen!

535
00:40:12,233 --> 00:40:15,700
I want you to go to the shelter
with Thomas. He's gonna
take you there now! Go!

536
00:40:15,766 --> 00:40:17,866
What's going on?
I don't have time
to explain, Willie.

537
00:40:17,933 --> 00:40:19,667
Just go with Thomas
and ring the bell. Now!

538
00:40:19,734 --> 00:40:22,799
What about my brother?
Your brother's with Mr. Benton.
Everybody, follow me!

539
00:40:22,866 --> 00:40:25,133
Juma's men are coming.
Do you have a weapon?

540
00:40:25,200 --> 00:40:27,899
How do you know this
isn't just another rumor?
Do you have a weapon or not?

541
00:40:27,966 --> 00:40:30,866
If they are coming,
I will talk to them.
They will listen to me.

542
00:40:30,933 --> 00:40:35,467
Save your helmet for the parade.
They are coming. Two of our boys
have already been shot.

543
00:40:35,533 --> 00:40:37,734
The United Nations
remains neutral
in this matter.

544
00:40:37,799 --> 00:40:39,600
You son of a bitch.

545
00:40:45,333 --> 00:40:48,333
You still want
to talk to them?
I didn't think so.

546
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:51,200
Why don't you
go hide in the shelter
with the other children?

547
00:40:51,267 --> 00:40:53,533
[ Bell Ringing ]
[ Willie Shouting ]

548
00:41:00,333 --> 00:41:02,766
[ Bell Ringing Continues ]
[ Shouting ]

549
00:41:04,600 --> 00:41:07,700
Willie! Enough. Let's go.
Let's go, Willie. Come on.

550
00:41:16,634 --> 00:41:20,133
Come on!
Hurry, hurry.

551
00:41:32,567 --> 00:41:34,600
[ Thomas ]
Boys, go!

552
00:41:36,866 --> 00:41:39,066
Come on, Russell!

553
00:41:54,700 --> 00:41:57,533
You're the last?
Yeah.

554
00:41:59,433 --> 00:42:01,866
Wait! Wait for me.

555
00:42:27,833 --> 00:42:29,799
[ Chattering ]

556
00:42:35,700 --> 00:42:37,634
[ Whistling ]

557
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:44,367
[ Man Speaking
Native Language ]
Go! Find the boys!

558
00:42:44,433 --> 00:42:47,600
Find them!

559
00:43:02,333 --> 00:43:04,766
Fire!

560
00:43:11,500 --> 00:43:13,799
Come!

561
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:19,033
[ Native Language Continues ]

562
00:44:16,899 --> 00:44:19,200
[ Grunts ]

563
00:44:40,333 --> 00:44:44,600
[ Man Shouting
In Native Language ]

564
00:44:46,799 --> 00:44:49,533
[ Shouting Continues ]

565
00:44:54,333 --> 00:44:56,500
[ Gunshot ]

566
00:45:23,700 --> 00:45:25,634
[ Youssou ]
Keep going! This way!

567
00:45:27,766 --> 00:45:30,367
There, there!
[ Gunshot ]

568
00:45:42,500 --> 00:45:44,367
[ Grunts ]

569
00:45:58,799 --> 00:46:00,734
[ Rifle Cocks ]
No.

570
00:46:01,734 --> 00:46:03,734
Do not kill him yet--

571
00:46:03,799 --> 00:46:06,400
Not until he tells us
where the children are hiding.

572
00:46:06,467 --> 00:46:08,400
Bring him.

573
00:46:35,133 --> 00:46:38,400
Stay here. Stay here.
Where are you going?

574
00:46:38,467 --> 00:46:40,467
I'll be back in a bit.

575
00:46:41,700 --> 00:46:44,367
[ Groaning ]

576
00:46:46,000 --> 00:46:48,033
[ Youssou ]
String him up.

577
00:46:49,166 --> 00:46:51,133
[ Native Language ]

578
00:46:54,233 --> 00:46:56,233
Tie him up.
Yeah.

579
00:46:58,533 --> 00:47:01,500
[ Chattering ]

580
00:47:01,567 --> 00:47:03,799
[ Youssou ]
I want him to suffer.

581
00:47:03,866 --> 00:47:05,866
[ Chattering ]

582
00:47:21,634 --> 00:47:26,233
U.S. citizens only.
What about her?
She's not American.

583
00:47:26,300 --> 00:47:29,267
She has family in the States.
I have a sister in Chicago.

584
00:47:29,333 --> 00:47:31,734
She has a job.
She needs to sponsor you.

585
00:47:31,799 --> 00:47:34,100
By then
it will be too late.

586
00:47:34,166 --> 00:47:36,533
My husband
died fighting Juma.
Juma will kill me.

587
00:47:36,600 --> 00:47:38,866
He will kill my child.

588
00:47:38,933 --> 00:47:42,500
There's a U.N. camp
across the eastern border.
How will I get there?

589
00:47:42,567 --> 00:47:46,933
I have no transportation.
The buses are all full.
I cannot walk.

590
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:49,066
I'm sorry.

591
00:47:49,133 --> 00:47:52,734
Whatever you want me
to do for you, I will do.

592
00:47:52,799 --> 00:47:55,467
Please.

593
00:47:55,533 --> 00:47:58,267
Just take me from here.

594
00:47:58,333 --> 00:48:00,267
[ Helicopter Whirring ]

595
00:48:00,333 --> 00:48:03,133
Anything at all.

596
00:48:03,200 --> 00:48:05,567
I can't. I'm sorry.

597
00:48:05,634 --> 00:48:07,933
Sir, it's Carl Benton.

598
00:48:09,233 --> 00:48:13,233
Please, don't let them
kill my baby!
Please! Please!

599
00:48:16,600 --> 00:48:18,866
- Benton.
- I've been trying to
get through to you.

600
00:48:18,933 --> 00:48:21,066
Yeah, our lines
are overloaded.
Juma's men are here.

601
00:48:21,133 --> 00:48:23,066
They're raising an army.
We know.

602
00:48:23,133 --> 00:48:26,433
You know?
Yeah, we don't know how
he managed to pull it off.

603
00:48:26,500 --> 00:48:29,766
No one saw it coming.
But he's got soldiers
moving in on the capital.

604
00:48:29,833 --> 00:48:32,333
They're here right now, Frank.
They're at my school.

605
00:48:32,400 --> 00:48:34,766
- You have to send
some marines to help.
- I can't spare any.

606
00:48:34,833 --> 00:48:37,367
They're all being deployed
for the evacuation.

607
00:48:37,433 --> 00:48:40,133
- Evacuation?
- The orders came down
from the president.

608
00:48:40,200 --> 00:48:44,000
We're rolling up all U.S.
nationals. We already started
ferrying people to the border.

609
00:48:44,066 --> 00:48:46,667
Look, I got 14 kids
hiding in a shelter,

610
00:48:46,734 --> 00:48:49,367
and one that's gonna bleed
to death if he doesn't get
medical attention.

611
00:48:49,433 --> 00:48:53,467
If you want us to get you out,
get here on your own. The last
chopper's leaving in an hour.

612
00:48:53,533 --> 00:48:56,233
Look, Frank. D-Don't
strand me like this, please.

613
00:48:56,300 --> 00:48:58,600
My hands are tied, Carl.
Frank-- Tramell, please.

614
00:48:58,667 --> 00:49:00,866
Sorry.
Please don't--
Damn it!

615
00:49:02,267 --> 00:49:04,200
[ Whispers ]
Damn it.

616
00:49:04,267 --> 00:49:06,233
[ Grunts ]

617
00:49:12,433 --> 00:49:15,367
I'm running out of ways
to ask the question.

618
00:49:15,433 --> 00:49:18,100
Where are the children?

619
00:49:23,567 --> 00:49:25,500
Again.

620
00:49:27,700 --> 00:49:31,700
- We have searched
all the buildings, sir.
- Keep looking.

621
00:49:33,833 --> 00:49:38,300
You're wasting your time.
They're not gonna find anything.
I told you they're not here.

622
00:49:38,367 --> 00:49:40,433
Wait.

623
00:49:41,933 --> 00:49:43,600
You're lying.

624
00:49:45,000 --> 00:49:47,634
No, I'm not.

625
00:49:48,933 --> 00:49:51,233
If you wanna find soldiers
for your army,

626
00:49:51,300 --> 00:49:54,300
you're gonna have to
look somewhere else.

627
00:49:58,000 --> 00:50:01,766
Where...
are the children?

628
00:50:01,833 --> 00:50:04,634
I told you--
I don't know.

629
00:50:06,066 --> 00:50:09,267
- [ Sizzling ]
- [ Jack Screaming ]

630
00:50:09,333 --> 00:50:11,500
[ Willie ]
Oh, Jack.

631
00:50:11,567 --> 00:50:15,467
[ Screaming Continues ]

632
00:50:21,400 --> 00:50:23,433
[ Grunts ]

633
00:50:37,700 --> 00:50:41,300
[ Grunting ]

634
00:50:41,367 --> 00:50:45,667
I will keep doing this
until you beg me to kill you.

635
00:50:45,734 --> 00:50:48,866
But I won't kill you
even then.
[ Grunts ]

636
00:50:48,933 --> 00:50:51,933
Not until you tell me...

637
00:50:52,000 --> 00:50:54,500
what I want to know.

638
00:50:54,567 --> 00:50:57,600
Please-- Please, no! No!

639
00:50:57,667 --> 00:51:01,000
I'll show you
where the kids are.
Tell me.

640
00:51:01,066 --> 00:51:04,100
I need to show you. They're
in an underground shelter.

641
00:51:04,166 --> 00:51:06,100
No.

642
00:51:06,166 --> 00:51:08,667
You will tell me
where this shelter is!

643
00:51:08,734 --> 00:51:11,000
Okay.

644
00:51:11,066 --> 00:51:13,933
About 200 meters
up the footpath.

645
00:51:14,000 --> 00:51:15,933
Behind the tree line.

646
00:51:16,000 --> 00:51:19,533
There's a wooden hatch
under a mound of dirt.
Please, just-- Please.

647
00:51:19,600 --> 00:51:22,799
[ Sobbing ]
Get the children.

648
00:51:25,233 --> 00:51:27,567
I will stay here
with him.

649
00:51:27,634 --> 00:51:29,866
Don't worry.

650
00:51:29,933 --> 00:51:34,567
Once I have these children,
I will kill you quickly.

651
00:51:36,267 --> 00:51:39,000
[ Groans ]

652
00:51:46,433 --> 00:51:49,433
[ Chamber Clicks Twice ]

653
00:51:50,600 --> 00:51:53,467
[ Gunshots ]

654
00:51:53,533 --> 00:51:55,500
[ Grunting ]

655
00:52:03,333 --> 00:52:05,267
- [ Yells ]
- [ Groans ]

656
00:52:06,634 --> 00:52:09,799
You all right, Jack?
Yeah. The kids
are in the shelter.

657
00:52:09,866 --> 00:52:12,734
How is Desmond?
He's lost
a lot of blood.

658
00:52:12,799 --> 00:52:16,433
The border's five hours
from here. I don't think
he's gonna make it.

659
00:52:16,500 --> 00:52:20,400
I'm gonna try and get 'em
to the embassy. They've
started evacuating already.

660
00:52:20,467 --> 00:52:23,300
How are you gonna get
the kids asylum?
They're not U.S. nationals.

661
00:52:23,367 --> 00:52:27,500
I've got sponsorship papers.
Tramell's got to let them in.

662
00:52:27,567 --> 00:52:30,734
But I have to go now, Jack.
The last chopper
leaves in an hour.

663
00:52:30,799 --> 00:52:32,600
You all right?
Go. Go!

664
00:52:32,667 --> 00:52:34,833
And, Jack, good luck.

665
00:52:44,600 --> 00:52:47,734
Stay here.
Jack may need our help.

666
00:52:47,799 --> 00:52:50,799
And if they catch you,
they will make you
tell them where we are.

667
00:52:50,866 --> 00:52:52,799
You are endangering
the rest of us.

668
00:52:52,866 --> 00:52:54,799
We wouldn't have
been in danger...

669
00:52:54,866 --> 00:52:57,766
if you had done something
about Juma instead of
looking the other way.

670
00:53:02,567 --> 00:53:05,899
Right. Everyone out.
Quickly.

671
00:53:05,966 --> 00:53:08,100
Go to the bus.
Quickly.

672
00:53:08,166 --> 00:53:12,400
Thomas, go get Desmond.
He's in the jeep
by the end of the footpath.

673
00:53:12,467 --> 00:53:15,933
Quickly, quickly, quickly.
Go to the bus.
Go to the bus. Go to the bus.

674
00:53:16,000 --> 00:53:18,799
Where is my brother?
Thomas has gone
to get him.

675
00:53:18,866 --> 00:53:21,367
Then he's all right?
He will be. He will be.
Go to the bus.

676
00:53:21,433 --> 00:53:23,133
Quickly, quickly.

677
00:53:27,133 --> 00:53:30,033
[ Chattering In
Native Language ]

678
00:53:30,100 --> 00:53:32,133
Desmond.

679
00:53:32,200 --> 00:53:35,600
It's not as bad
as it looks.

680
00:53:36,899 --> 00:53:39,100
Wait. Listen up!
Listen up!

681
00:53:39,166 --> 00:53:43,066
Everyone, listen.
We're taking the bus
into the city.

682
00:53:43,133 --> 00:53:46,367
Once we're on the road
I'll explain everything
that's happening. All right?

683
00:53:46,433 --> 00:53:49,300
But we have to move now.
On the bus. Move.
Quickly. Quickly.

684
00:53:49,367 --> 00:53:52,634
Solenz!
Where you going?

685
00:53:52,700 --> 00:53:57,467
I told Mr. Bauer before.
The United Nations remains
neutral in this conflict.

686
00:53:57,533 --> 00:54:00,833
A U.N. escort might help us
get where we need to go.

687
00:54:02,033 --> 00:54:04,933
Solenz!
[ Jack ]
Let him go!

688
00:54:05,000 --> 00:54:09,000
He's just trying to save
his own ass because he knows
the children are a target.

689
00:54:10,467 --> 00:54:12,400
You're gonna need
my help, Carl.

690
00:54:12,467 --> 00:54:16,433
Juma's men are gonna set up
roadblocks, checkpoints
all the way into the city.

691
00:54:16,500 --> 00:54:20,066
I got one of the soldiers'
walkies. We can use it
to try and avoid them.

692
00:54:20,133 --> 00:54:23,066
Jack, you won't have to go
anywhere near the embassy.

693
00:54:23,133 --> 00:54:26,233
Just help me get the kids
to the city. You can head
to the border from there.

694
00:54:26,300 --> 00:54:28,333
Let's go.

695
00:54:47,433 --> 00:54:50,667
Can you take it easy?
Just keep your hands
where I can see 'em.

696
00:54:50,734 --> 00:54:53,667
I told you,
he's expecting me.
Hey, Rog!

697
00:54:53,734 --> 00:54:56,833
R-Rog, can you call
your watchdog off, please?

698
00:54:56,899 --> 00:55:00,200
Agent Vossler,
he's a friend of mine.
You can let him in.

699
00:55:02,000 --> 00:55:04,899
Your friend's
jacked up on something.

700
00:55:04,966 --> 00:55:06,899
I'll take care of it.
It's all right.

701
00:55:06,966 --> 00:55:08,899
I'll be outside.
Thank you.

702
00:55:10,233 --> 00:55:12,166
Look, man, um,

703
00:55:12,233 --> 00:55:15,700
I know that my timing
right now must,
you know, suck.

704
00:55:15,766 --> 00:55:19,899
So thank you. It's just,
I'm-- I think I'm in a
little bit of trouble here.

705
00:55:19,966 --> 00:55:22,833
So--
What kind of trouble?
Coke? Pills?

706
00:55:22,899 --> 00:55:25,166
Don't get all righteous
on me, Rog. Okay?

707
00:55:25,233 --> 00:55:28,333
I seem to remember
most nights you partying me
under the table.

708
00:55:28,400 --> 00:55:31,200
- That was a long time ago.
- Not that long ago.

709
00:55:32,600 --> 00:55:34,667
You got five minutes,
so talk fast.

710
00:55:37,799 --> 00:55:40,734
Uh, okay.

711
00:55:40,799 --> 00:55:43,634
Couple months ago Nichols
calls me into his office.

712
00:55:43,700 --> 00:55:46,300
Says he wants me to manage
a special project.

713
00:55:46,367 --> 00:55:48,333
Special project?
That's what he calls it.

714
00:55:48,400 --> 00:55:51,667
He says he knows I've
taken some serious hits
in the stock market,

715
00:55:51,734 --> 00:55:55,133
and he's gonna
give me a chance
to recover my losses.

716
00:55:55,200 --> 00:55:57,567
I mean, the money
he paid me-- Rog.

717
00:55:57,634 --> 00:56:00,000
[ Chuckling ]
It was crazy.

718
00:56:00,066 --> 00:56:01,933
I mean, the money
was really crazy.

719
00:56:02,000 --> 00:56:05,300
All I had to do was
keep my mouth shut.
What'd he have you do, Chris?

720
00:56:05,367 --> 00:56:08,600
Open a few offshore accounts,
move money in and out,
that type of thing.

721
00:56:08,667 --> 00:56:11,333
So you helped Nichols
embezzle money
from his own firm.

722
00:56:11,400 --> 00:56:14,300
Yeah, that's what I thought
I was doing at first.

723
00:56:14,367 --> 00:56:18,066
But, Rog, three days ago
I recognized the prefix
on one of the accounts.

724
00:56:18,133 --> 00:56:21,567
It's something the Justice
Department has red-flagged
for traders to report.

725
00:56:21,634 --> 00:56:25,899
So, I do a little digging
and, uh,

726
00:56:29,133 --> 00:56:32,400
turns out that the, uh--
the account holder...

727
00:56:32,467 --> 00:56:34,866
is on the terrorist
watch list.

728
00:56:36,033 --> 00:56:38,066
Yeah. Yeah.

729
00:56:38,133 --> 00:56:40,066
Who is it?
I don't know.

730
00:56:40,133 --> 00:56:42,066
I don't know, Rog.
I don't wanna know.

731
00:56:42,133 --> 00:56:45,066
Frankly, it's all getting
a little too weird for me.

732
00:56:45,133 --> 00:56:47,933
This morning
there was this creepy guy
in Nichols's office who--

733
00:56:48,933 --> 00:56:51,033
Look, I don't know
what he's doing.

734
00:56:51,100 --> 00:56:54,033
I don't want to have
anything to do with it.

735
00:56:54,100 --> 00:56:56,000
I'm willing to turn
state's evidence.

736
00:56:56,066 --> 00:56:59,066
Yeah? Good.
You should go to the F.B.I.

737
00:57:00,533 --> 00:57:02,667
Man, I was just thinking
that, uh--

738
00:57:02,734 --> 00:57:05,700
[ Sniffs ]
I could probably cut
a much better deal...

739
00:57:05,766 --> 00:57:08,500
if we take this
directly to your mother.

740
00:57:10,133 --> 00:57:13,233
Y-You want my mother
to clean up your mess?

741
00:57:13,300 --> 00:57:16,866
Chris, what do you expect me
to say to that?
I don't know, Rog.

742
00:57:16,933 --> 00:57:18,866
Uh, how about,

743
00:57:18,933 --> 00:57:22,433
"I'm sorry to hear
that you're in trouble, Chris,
but you're a friend of mine...

744
00:57:22,500 --> 00:57:26,033
and I'm gonna do whatever
I can do to help you out"?

745
00:57:27,734 --> 00:57:30,866
[ Sighs ]

746
00:57:30,933 --> 00:57:32,933
Do you even have
any evidence?

747
00:57:33,000 --> 00:57:34,966
[ Scoffs ]

748
00:57:37,667 --> 00:57:40,567
- I'm working on it.
- What does that mean?

749
00:57:40,634 --> 00:57:43,000
What does it mean?
It means, um--

750
00:57:45,533 --> 00:57:49,100
Nichols asked me
to destroy some records.
I didn't do it.

751
00:57:49,166 --> 00:57:53,133
I, um-- I sent them
to my hard drive
at home instead.

752
00:57:53,200 --> 00:57:56,066
They're coded, but, you know,
they're probably traceable.

753
00:57:56,133 --> 00:57:58,267
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

754
00:57:59,799 --> 00:58:01,766
- Hello, Chris.
- Hey, Sam.

755
00:58:01,833 --> 00:58:04,866
- You look great.
- Thank you.

756
00:58:04,933 --> 00:58:07,267
We really need to leave now.
We're already pushing it.

757
00:58:07,333 --> 00:58:10,634
Agent Vossler's
in the car waiting.
I'll meet you there.

758
00:58:11,634 --> 00:58:14,233
I'm right behind you.

759
00:58:14,300 --> 00:58:16,133
[ Whispers ]
Okay.

760
00:58:16,200 --> 00:58:18,634
- See you at work later?
- Right.

761
00:58:20,933 --> 00:58:22,600
[ Door Closes ]

762
00:58:22,667 --> 00:58:25,267
I have to go.
I know.
I know, I know, I know.

763
00:58:25,333 --> 00:58:28,433
If I forward you these records,
will you at least
show them to your mother?

764
00:58:28,500 --> 00:58:32,100
I'm not talking to anybody
until I see them for myself.
Okay, all right. That's--

765
00:58:32,166 --> 00:58:34,133
Look, Rog,

766
00:58:34,200 --> 00:58:35,799
thank you.

767
00:58:35,866 --> 00:58:37,799
Just check your e-mail
in one hour.

768
00:58:37,866 --> 00:58:40,166
Clean yourself up.
Okay?

769
00:58:40,233 --> 00:58:42,267
Yeah.

770
00:58:44,000 --> 00:58:46,533
[ Men Chattering ]
Sixteen mortar teams supported
by 20 forward observers.

771
00:58:46,600 --> 00:58:49,700
Make sure we all have
the same encryption codes.

772
00:58:49,766 --> 00:58:53,467
And have a backup
in case government try to
jam communication.

773
00:58:53,533 --> 00:58:56,267
Sir, General Juma
is here.

774
00:59:03,833 --> 00:59:05,766
Welcome home, General.

775
00:59:07,467 --> 00:59:09,467
Colonel Dubaku.

776
00:59:10,533 --> 00:59:13,400
Look what you've built here.

777
00:59:13,467 --> 00:59:16,899
Our American friends
have been very helpful.

778
00:59:16,966 --> 00:59:19,100
Did they send us
the Howitzers?
Yes.

779
00:59:19,166 --> 00:59:22,933
We have them in position
about 20 kilometers
from the capital.

780
00:59:23,000 --> 00:59:25,267
We can hit any target
in the city.

781
00:59:25,333 --> 00:59:28,500
All we need is your order
to begin the bombardment.

782
00:59:29,700 --> 00:59:32,267
Sir.
One of our checkpoints.

783
00:59:32,333 --> 00:59:34,966
Excuse me, General.

784
00:59:35,033 --> 00:59:38,600
- Yes?
- Colonel, this is
Lieutenant Kintu.

785
00:59:38,667 --> 00:59:40,367
Checkpoint Delta.

786
00:59:40,433 --> 00:59:43,367
We have a man in custody,
a U.N. relief worker.

787
00:59:43,433 --> 00:59:46,866
He was driving to his base,
but we have detained him
for questioning.

788
00:59:46,933 --> 00:59:49,899
He says he has information
about your brother.

789
00:59:49,966 --> 00:59:53,866
- What sort of information?
- He says your brother
is dead, sir.

790
00:59:53,933 --> 00:59:55,866
[ Gasps Quietly ]
No.

791
00:59:55,933 --> 00:59:58,966
Your brother and his men,
they were ambushed
at the American school.

792
00:59:59,033 --> 01:00:04,333
He says that he can
help us find the man
who killed your brother.

793
01:00:13,899 --> 01:00:15,899
Hold it steady.

794
01:00:17,300 --> 01:00:21,833
[ Groaning ]

795
01:00:35,799 --> 01:00:37,966
Good.
Thank you, Willie.

796
01:00:40,367 --> 01:00:43,333
Desmond,
you sure the bandage
isn't too tight?

797
01:00:43,400 --> 01:00:45,367
Yeah.

798
01:00:48,799 --> 01:00:50,799
Be right back.

799
01:00:55,367 --> 01:00:58,300
Managed to stop the bleeding,
but Desmond's fever is spiking.

800
01:00:58,367 --> 01:01:02,100
If we don't get him
to a hospital soon,
he's gonna go into shock.

801
01:01:02,166 --> 01:01:05,300
We're five kilometers
from the city.

802
01:01:05,367 --> 01:01:08,267
Carl, I'm really sorry
about the school.

803
01:01:08,333 --> 01:01:11,267
I know how much
you put into it.

804
01:01:11,333 --> 01:01:14,267
Just a bunch of cement
and two-by-fours, right?

805
01:01:14,333 --> 01:01:16,267
What the hell
was I thinking,

806
01:01:16,333 --> 01:01:19,533
letting myself
believe that things
were finally different here,

807
01:01:19,600 --> 01:01:22,166
that this country
had turned a corner?

808
01:01:22,233 --> 01:01:25,400
[ Dubaku On Radio ]
The bus is from
the American school.

809
01:01:25,467 --> 01:01:28,000
They are heading into the city
from the Okavango.

810
01:01:28,066 --> 01:01:32,333
There is only one
of two roads they can go.
I'm seeing patrols on both.

811
01:01:32,400 --> 01:01:34,333
[ Man On Radio ]
Sir, this is Patrol One.

812
01:01:34,400 --> 01:01:36,833
We have not seen a bus
matching that description.

813
01:01:36,899 --> 01:01:40,100
- Where is your position?
- Heading east, one kilometer
west of Okavango Junction.

814
01:01:40,166 --> 01:01:43,866
-Jack, they're
right in front of us.
-Let me know when you have them.

815
01:01:43,933 --> 01:01:46,500
Everybody hold on!
Hold on!

816
01:01:48,433 --> 01:01:51,233
[ Children Shouting,
Chattering ]

817
01:01:53,567 --> 01:01:55,667
[ Engine Off ]
Quiet.

818
01:01:55,734 --> 01:01:58,500
What is it?
Rebel patrol.

819
01:02:03,333 --> 01:02:06,533
[ Jeep Passing By ]

820
01:02:06,600 --> 01:02:08,966
Carl, we can't
get back on that road.

821
01:02:09,033 --> 01:02:13,100
We'll walk to the embassy.
If we follow the river,
it'll take us to the city.

822
01:02:13,166 --> 01:02:16,600
- Desmond will not
make it that far.
- Then you help him, Thomas.

823
01:02:16,667 --> 01:02:19,667
We're not getting back
on that road.

824
01:02:19,734 --> 01:02:22,200
[ Willie ]
Where are we going?
[ Carl ] To the embassy.

825
01:02:22,267 --> 01:02:24,267
Let's go!
Quickly! Quickly!

826
01:02:29,966 --> 01:02:32,300
[ Whispering ]
Hurry up. Hurry up.
Quickly.

827
01:02:32,367 --> 01:02:35,667
Quickly. I'll take him.
I'll take him.

828
01:02:35,734 --> 01:02:37,200
Take this.
Take this.

829
01:02:37,267 --> 01:02:39,066
[ Whispers ]
Stay here.

830
01:02:42,966 --> 01:02:46,133
[ Carl ] Willie!
Willie, hurry up!

831
01:02:55,033 --> 01:02:56,966
Your wife will be out
in a minute.

832
01:02:57,033 --> 01:03:01,333
She'd better be, or she's gonna
be late for her inauguration.
What's going on in there?

833
01:03:01,400 --> 01:03:03,333
Well, I really can't
discuss that,

834
01:03:03,400 --> 01:03:05,634
but, of course,
when your wife comes out...

835
01:03:05,700 --> 01:03:07,700
you're certainly free
to ask her.

836
01:03:07,766 --> 01:03:10,367
I asked you
a simple question, Tom.

837
01:03:10,433 --> 01:03:12,634
If you can't answer it,
fine.

838
01:03:12,700 --> 01:03:15,233
But I don't need your permission
to talk to my wife.

839
01:03:16,400 --> 01:03:18,799
Well, I would hope not.

840
01:03:18,866 --> 01:03:23,533
If you will excuse me,
I have to continue
packing up my office.

841
01:03:37,567 --> 01:03:39,567
The decision book.

842
01:03:40,899 --> 01:03:43,333
Master protocols
for the command and control...

843
01:03:43,400 --> 01:03:45,833
of our nuclear arsenal.

844
01:03:48,600 --> 01:03:51,600
I never knew
how much I didn't know
till I read that book.

845
01:03:52,667 --> 01:03:54,433
Are the gold codes
in here?

846
01:03:54,500 --> 01:03:56,333
Not yet.

847
01:03:57,500 --> 01:04:01,433
Dan Wilcox will deliver them
to your designate.

848
01:04:03,200 --> 01:04:07,133
All right then.
Well, if we're finished here
I should get going.

849
01:04:07,200 --> 01:04:10,866
Join me for a drink,
a toast to your administration.

850
01:04:10,933 --> 01:04:14,799
As much as I'd like to,
it's still a little early
in the morning.

851
01:04:14,866 --> 01:04:17,533
- You sure?
- Yes.

852
01:04:22,433 --> 01:04:24,200
To your administration.

853
01:04:25,233 --> 01:04:27,734
Thank you.

854
01:04:27,799 --> 01:04:30,400
Thank you, Mr. President.

855
01:04:32,899 --> 01:04:35,766
Thank you, Mr. President.

856
01:04:43,833 --> 01:04:47,899
Please extend my gratitude
to your transition team...

857
01:04:47,966 --> 01:04:49,966
for all they've done.

858
01:04:54,200 --> 01:04:57,200
You know what
the talking heads are saying?

859
01:05:00,100 --> 01:05:03,433
They're saying that
I lost this election
because I didn't want to win it.

860
01:05:03,500 --> 01:05:07,533
They're saying that...
my heart wasn't in it.

861
01:05:11,799 --> 01:05:13,799
What about you?

862
01:05:14,933 --> 01:05:16,933
Me?

863
01:05:17,000 --> 01:05:19,300
Do you agree
with their opinion?

864
01:05:22,166 --> 01:05:26,133
I don't believe
there's a simple answer
to that question.

865
01:05:26,200 --> 01:05:29,734
[ Laughing ]

866
01:05:29,799 --> 01:05:32,133
You are right.

867
01:05:32,200 --> 01:05:35,133
Nothing about this job
lends itself to simple answers,

868
01:05:35,200 --> 01:05:37,367
just, uh,

869
01:05:37,433 --> 01:05:39,634
jagged edges and moving parts,

870
01:05:39,700 --> 01:05:43,300
most you won't even see coming
till they've smacked you
in the head.

871
01:05:47,933 --> 01:05:50,166
So, uh,

872
01:05:54,833 --> 01:05:57,100
be careful,

873
01:05:57,166 --> 01:05:59,467
Madam President.

874
01:06:04,700 --> 01:06:06,833
See you at the inauguration.

875
01:06:18,166 --> 01:06:20,700
[ Man Chattering,
Indistinct ]

876
01:06:23,467 --> 01:06:25,933
Are you all right?
I'm not sure yet.

877
01:06:26,000 --> 01:06:27,899
Gentlemen.

878
01:06:27,966 --> 01:06:31,300
We just got word
of a coup in Sangala.

879
01:06:31,367 --> 01:06:35,000
Daniels has ordered
the embassy to evacuate
without even consulting me.

880
01:06:35,066 --> 01:06:39,000
Is it the right call?
Right or wrong, he should have
brought me in on the decision.

881
01:06:39,066 --> 01:06:41,500
Maybe he's still bitter
about the election.

882
01:06:41,567 --> 01:06:44,433
Noah Daniels
isn't that vindictive.

883
01:06:44,500 --> 01:06:50,066
You think he has a reason
for pulling out of Sangala
before you take office.

884
01:06:50,133 --> 01:06:52,066
Maybe.

885
01:06:52,133 --> 01:06:54,799
I'll call Ethan from the car.

886
01:06:54,866 --> 01:06:59,799
If Daniels is
hiding anything about Sangala,
he'll be able to dig it up.

887
01:06:59,866 --> 01:07:02,267
[ Man On Radio ]
It's definitely the bus
from Okavango.

888
01:07:02,333 --> 01:07:05,267
They were here not too long ago,
at least a dozen boys.

889
01:07:05,333 --> 01:07:08,033
I don't care how many boys.
How many men? Just Benton?

890
01:07:08,100 --> 01:07:11,166
- Or is he with that bastard
that killed my brother?
- There were two men.

891
01:07:12,933 --> 01:07:16,267
- Along the river would
be their fastest route.
- Good.

892
01:07:16,333 --> 01:07:21,433
Colonel Dubaku, I am sorry
to hear about your brother,
but I need you here.

893
01:07:23,367 --> 01:07:25,367
Are you ordering me
to stay?

894
01:07:25,433 --> 01:07:30,300
A campaign is just beginning,
and you are critical
to its success.

895
01:07:30,367 --> 01:07:34,833
There will be time
for you to avenge your brother
after we have taken power.

896
01:07:38,033 --> 01:07:39,966
The man
who killed my brother...

897
01:07:40,033 --> 01:07:42,000
is heading toward
the American embassy.

898
01:07:42,066 --> 01:07:44,500
They are evacuating
within an hour.

899
01:07:44,567 --> 01:07:48,899
That is all the time I have
and all the time I need.

900
01:07:49,966 --> 01:07:52,734
Sir!
Excuse me, General.

901
01:07:52,799 --> 01:07:54,799
Sir, the men
are ready, sir.

902
01:07:56,033 --> 01:07:58,033
Go.

903
01:08:00,833 --> 01:08:02,799
Go.

904
01:08:12,799 --> 01:08:15,400
[ Anchorman ]
President-elect Taylor...

905
01:08:15,467 --> 01:08:18,467
will make her way to the steps
of the U.S. Capitol where,

906
01:08:18,533 --> 01:08:20,833
standing before thousands
of American citizens and--

907
01:09:04,600 --> 01:09:06,600
[ Sighs ]

908
01:09:08,866 --> 01:09:11,433
[ Beeping ]

909
01:09:18,100 --> 01:09:20,367
[ Pills Rattling ]

910
01:09:29,700 --> 01:09:31,700
[ Thumps ]

911
01:10:26,833 --> 01:10:29,933
Is this everything,
Mr. Whitley?

912
01:10:38,567 --> 01:10:40,933
You've been stealing
financial records
from your office.

913
01:10:41,000 --> 01:10:44,899
Those files are private property
and I'm here to recover them.

914
01:10:44,966 --> 01:10:47,000
Is this everything?

915
01:10:50,066 --> 01:10:54,433
Uh, look, I-- I saw something
didn't look right,
took it home to check it out.

916
01:10:54,500 --> 01:10:57,700
It's probably a mistake--
Just calm down.
Answer my question.

917
01:11:01,467 --> 01:11:04,400
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
That's everything.
It's all there.

918
01:11:04,467 --> 01:11:07,833
- What about your laptop?
- Um, it's, uh--

919
01:11:07,899 --> 01:11:11,200
- It's in my briefcase,
if you want to check it.
- Did you make any hard copies?

920
01:11:11,267 --> 01:11:13,367
No, I swear--

921
01:11:13,433 --> 01:11:16,667
I-- I barely even
looked at those files.

922
01:11:16,734 --> 01:11:20,200
- Who have you shown them to?
- No one. N-Nobody.

923
01:11:33,000 --> 01:11:35,400
So, um,

924
01:11:35,467 --> 01:11:39,233
just erase it,
take whatever you want,
then you leave.

925
01:11:43,166 --> 01:11:45,166
Okay?
Are we cool?

926
01:11:45,233 --> 01:11:48,233
Whoa. Whoa!
Hey, do we look
like fools to you?

927
01:11:48,300 --> 01:11:52,033
Huh? Do we?
Do we?
No! No! No!

928
01:11:52,100 --> 01:11:54,066
Then don't talk to us
like we are.

929
01:11:54,133 --> 01:11:56,166
Okay--
Sit down.

930
01:11:58,700 --> 01:12:01,734
Open your shirt,
Mr. Whitley.
Why?

931
01:12:01,799 --> 01:12:05,033
Your shirt.
What are you doing?

932
01:12:05,100 --> 01:12:08,066
You're going to tell us
everything you know,

933
01:12:08,133 --> 01:12:10,433
and we'll know
if you're lying.

934
01:12:14,500 --> 01:12:18,200
Just leave it alone, okay?
Chris asked me
not to tell anyone.

935
01:12:18,267 --> 01:12:20,300
I am not "anyone."
Come on, Sam.

936
01:12:20,367 --> 01:12:22,400
I don't trust him.
Then trust me.

937
01:12:26,100 --> 01:12:29,200
- We're here, sir.
- You made great time, Edward.

938
01:12:31,100 --> 01:12:33,000
[ People Chattering ]

939
01:12:33,066 --> 01:12:36,000
Look, I know that Chris
is your friend.

940
01:12:36,066 --> 01:12:39,033
It's just this idea of you
having a secret with him--

941
01:12:39,100 --> 01:12:41,600
I gave him my word
I wouldn't tell anyone.

942
01:12:41,667 --> 01:12:43,799
You need to
respect that. Okay?

943
01:12:43,866 --> 01:12:46,300
[ Sighs ]

944
01:12:46,367 --> 01:12:48,600
Okay?

945
01:12:48,667 --> 01:12:50,700
Okay.

946
01:12:50,766 --> 01:12:52,734
Okay.

947
01:12:52,799 --> 01:12:55,200
Big turnout.
[ Shutters Clicking ]

948
01:12:55,267 --> 01:12:59,433
It's crazy having a mother
who's the hottest
ticket in town.

949
01:13:00,766 --> 01:13:03,500
[ Chattering Continues ]

950
01:13:04,500 --> 01:13:06,634
[ Phone Ringing ]

951
01:13:09,400 --> 01:13:13,066
Vossler.
It took some doing, but we
managed to recover the files.

952
01:13:13,133 --> 01:13:15,066
What's our exposure?

953
01:13:15,133 --> 01:13:17,833
Unclear.
We're working on it now.

954
01:13:17,899 --> 01:13:19,734
Find out
and call me back.

955
01:13:19,799 --> 01:13:21,766
[ Woman ]
Hi. How are you?

956
01:13:21,833 --> 01:13:25,166
[ Chris Whimpering ]

957
01:13:27,267 --> 01:13:29,467
[ Muffled Screaming ]

958
01:13:40,400 --> 01:13:42,333
Clear.

959
01:13:43,899 --> 01:13:46,133
Willie.

960
01:13:46,200 --> 01:13:48,533
Take Desmond.
That's it.

961
01:13:48,600 --> 01:13:51,333
Thomas,
stay close, okay?

962
01:13:53,233 --> 01:13:55,367
Jack.

963
01:13:55,433 --> 01:13:59,367
There's a road
through those trees,
takes us to the city.

964
01:13:59,433 --> 01:14:01,634
We should be safe
when we get there.

965
01:14:01,700 --> 01:14:05,866
You follow the riverbed.
That'll take you
to the border.

966
01:14:05,933 --> 01:14:08,033
You'll get there
before dark.
You sure?

967
01:14:08,100 --> 01:14:10,333
Jack, we'll be fine.

968
01:14:10,400 --> 01:14:13,400
Thanks for helping us
get this far.

969
01:14:18,700 --> 01:14:21,300
Yeah.

970
01:14:22,333 --> 01:14:24,634
You take care of yourself.
Always.

971
01:14:34,567 --> 01:14:38,233
[ Helicopter Rotors
Whirring, Faint ]

972
01:14:39,233 --> 01:14:41,267
Carl. Carl.

973
01:14:41,333 --> 01:14:44,467
[ Rotors Continue Whirring,
Louder ]

974
01:14:50,166 --> 01:14:52,667
Kids in the trees.
In the trees! Now! Move!

975
01:14:52,734 --> 01:14:55,833
[ Carl ]
Run! Quickly!

976
01:15:18,133 --> 01:15:20,200
There.
Line them up.

977
01:15:20,267 --> 01:15:22,766
Hurry up! Hurry up!

978
01:15:22,833 --> 01:15:26,233
Take cover! Take cover!
Hurry up!

979
01:15:26,300 --> 01:15:28,766
- Fire!
- Take cover! Quickly!

980
01:15:28,833 --> 01:15:31,799
[ Jack ]
Boys, keep running!
Keep running! Don't look back!

981
01:15:31,866 --> 01:15:33,833
Keep running!

982
01:15:35,333 --> 01:15:39,133
- Move!
- [ Machine Gun Fire Continues ]

983
01:15:48,133 --> 01:15:49,766
Now he's coming behind.

984
01:15:49,833 --> 01:15:52,267
[ Rifle Cocks ]
I got a shot.
Roll 'em out.

985
01:15:52,333 --> 01:15:54,066
Now!

986
01:15:56,433 --> 01:15:58,667
- [ Gunshots ]
- [ Machine Gun Fire ]

987
01:16:15,066 --> 01:16:17,966
They're going down.
Go, boys! Come on!
Now! Hurry up!

988
01:16:18,033 --> 01:16:20,333
Go! Go! Go!

989
01:16:20,400 --> 01:16:22,799
Go!

990
01:16:22,866 --> 01:16:25,899
Pull it up! Pull it up!

991
01:16:25,966 --> 01:16:28,400
[ Alarm Blaring ]

992
01:16:40,700 --> 01:16:43,367
[ Jack ]
Come on.

993
01:16:48,734 --> 01:16:50,766
Come on.

994
01:16:53,634 --> 01:16:56,433
It's all right.
Let's go.

995
01:17:00,300 --> 01:17:02,200
[ Whispering ]
Willie, come back.
Come back.

996
01:17:05,033 --> 01:17:07,600
Willie, get back here.

997
01:17:09,799 --> 01:17:11,766
Stop. Stop!

998
01:17:11,833 --> 01:17:13,799
Don't-- Don't move!

999
01:17:13,866 --> 01:17:15,933
[ Clicks ]

1000
01:17:17,634 --> 01:17:20,333
Jack!

1001
01:17:20,400 --> 01:17:23,833
Stay there.
Don't move.
Don't come near me.

1002
01:17:23,899 --> 01:17:27,066
- I didn't want to leave this.
- I know, I know.
It's all right.

1003
01:17:32,367 --> 01:17:35,033
Go with Thomas.

1004
01:17:35,100 --> 01:17:38,899
Willie, it's all right.
Come with me.
Slowly. Slowly.

1005
01:17:38,966 --> 01:17:41,966
Stay on the path.
Go with the other boys.
Go.

1006
01:17:44,833 --> 01:17:49,100
Forget it, Jack. Just go.
Take the kids and go.

1007
01:17:55,567 --> 01:17:58,567
Damn it, Jack.
There's nothing we can do.

1008
01:17:59,966 --> 01:18:02,100
There. Okay.

1009
01:18:02,166 --> 01:18:05,600
It's round,
in a gray casing,

1010
01:18:05,667 --> 01:18:08,400
with a Cyrillic "b"
and the number "291"
stenciled on the side.

1011
01:18:08,467 --> 01:18:10,866
Spring-loaded.
Russian antipersonnel mine.

1012
01:18:10,933 --> 01:18:13,567
Five kilo.
I take my weight off,
and that's it.

1013
01:18:13,634 --> 01:18:15,799
I'm gonna try and disassemble
the trigger mechanism.

1014
01:18:15,866 --> 01:18:18,899
- It's got
an anti-tamper system.
- I'll find a work-around.

1015
01:18:18,966 --> 01:18:23,333
-Even if you had the tools,
it'd take more than an hour.
-There's gotta be a kill switch.

1016
01:18:23,400 --> 01:18:25,333
There's no time, Jack.
Stop.

1017
01:18:25,400 --> 01:18:27,300
Just give me a second.
Jack, stop.

1018
01:18:27,367 --> 01:18:29,333
Stop!

1019
01:18:36,567 --> 01:18:39,300
It's all right, Jack.

1020
01:18:39,367 --> 01:18:41,233
I can die like this.

1021
01:18:41,300 --> 01:18:44,866
Just-- Just take the kids
to the embassy.
Make sure they're safe.

1022
01:18:44,933 --> 01:18:46,899
Carl, don't do this.

1023
01:18:46,966 --> 01:18:48,899
Shh, shh, shh.

1024
01:18:48,966 --> 01:18:51,267
Take--
Take these papers.

1025
01:18:51,333 --> 01:18:53,267
Sponsorship papers.

1026
01:18:53,333 --> 01:18:55,667
Give them to Tramell.

1027
01:18:55,734 --> 01:18:58,400
Please, Jack.
Please.

1028
01:19:04,567 --> 01:19:08,467
Give me the rifle.
I'm gonna buy you
some time, Jack.

1029
01:19:08,533 --> 01:19:10,634
Maybe more.

1030
01:19:12,433 --> 01:19:14,500
Yeah.

1031
01:19:26,300 --> 01:19:28,734
Go on.

1032
01:19:28,799 --> 01:19:31,367
Go.

1033
01:19:31,433 --> 01:19:33,433
Go. Go.

1034
01:19:44,734 --> 01:19:48,966
Go ahead with Jack.
I'll be right behind.

1035
01:19:49,033 --> 01:19:52,066
- Mr. Benton!
- I'll catch up.

1036
01:19:54,133 --> 01:19:56,100
Go. Go.

1037
01:19:56,166 --> 01:19:58,100
We gotta go.
We gotta go.

1038
01:19:58,166 --> 01:20:00,166
Please. Come on.
Let's go.

1039
01:20:03,033 --> 01:20:05,033
[ Thomas ]
Let's go.

1040
01:20:13,333 --> 01:20:16,333
[ Sobbing ]

1041
01:20:18,367 --> 01:20:21,400
[ Men Chattering
In Native Language ]

1042
01:20:25,267 --> 01:20:28,866
Yes.
Okay, I'll tell him.

1043
01:20:28,933 --> 01:20:31,734
Colonel. Sir.

1044
01:20:31,799 --> 01:20:34,333
We cannot follow them
into the city.

1045
01:20:34,400 --> 01:20:36,400
It's still under
government control.

1046
01:20:38,367 --> 01:20:40,634
Since when do you
start giving orders?

1047
01:20:40,700 --> 01:20:42,634
I spoke to Udo.

1048
01:20:42,700 --> 01:20:45,367
He has some men...

1049
01:20:45,433 --> 01:20:47,634
inside the city
looking for him,

1050
01:20:47,700 --> 01:20:50,200
looking for Benton
and the other man.

1051
01:20:50,267 --> 01:20:53,200
With the children
they won't be hard to find.

1052
01:20:53,267 --> 01:20:56,200
Well, I will find them
and kill them myself,

1053
01:20:56,267 --> 01:20:58,634
even if I have to
go into the city.

1054
01:20:58,700 --> 01:21:01,200
Go. Find them.

1055
01:21:09,600 --> 01:21:11,966
[ Chattering Continues ]

1056
01:21:14,567 --> 01:21:17,000
Colonel Dubaku, look.

1057
01:21:18,433 --> 01:21:21,333
[ Chattering Continues ]

1058
01:21:21,400 --> 01:21:24,066
Go.

1059
01:21:24,133 --> 01:21:27,600
[ Native Language ]

1060
01:21:38,734 --> 01:21:40,667
Who are you?

1061
01:21:40,734 --> 01:21:43,634
I'm Benton.

1062
01:21:43,700 --> 01:21:46,533
- Where is your friend?
- Which one?

1063
01:21:47,933 --> 01:21:49,799
[ Screams ]

1064
01:21:55,700 --> 01:21:57,700
Where is he?

1065
01:21:58,866 --> 01:22:01,133
I don't know
what you're talking about.

1066
01:22:04,433 --> 01:22:08,133
[ Groans ]

1067
01:22:08,200 --> 01:22:10,433
[ Panting ]
All right.

1068
01:22:12,200 --> 01:22:14,200
All right.

1069
01:22:14,267 --> 01:22:16,500
[ Muttering ]
He's taking them--

1070
01:22:18,100 --> 01:22:20,500
- What?
- He's taking them--

1071
01:22:21,567 --> 01:22:23,500
What are you saying?
Hmm?

1072
01:22:23,567 --> 01:22:26,433
What are you saying?
He's taking them to--
[ Groans ]

1073
01:22:26,500 --> 01:22:28,367
Bring him to me.

1074
01:22:28,433 --> 01:22:30,467
[ Groans ]

1075
01:22:33,734 --> 01:22:35,766
Go to hell.

1076
01:22:37,000 --> 01:22:39,933
[ Explosion ]

1077
01:22:47,634 --> 01:22:50,166
What was that?
Nothing.
Just keep moving.

1078
01:22:50,233 --> 01:22:52,166
Come with me.
Go on.

1079
01:22:52,233 --> 01:22:54,233
Come on. Move.

1080
01:23:35,933 --> 01:23:39,899
Nice to see you.
Congratulations
to your family.

1081
01:23:39,966 --> 01:23:42,833
** [ "Stars and Stripes
Forever" ]

1082
01:23:46,233 --> 01:23:49,100
- Expecting a call?
- Hmm?

1083
01:23:49,166 --> 01:23:52,333
It's about Chris, isn't it?
He was supposed to send me
something 15 minutes ago.

1084
01:23:52,400 --> 01:23:55,700
Call him later.
Your mother's here.

1085
01:24:01,933 --> 01:24:05,267
[ Shutters Clicking ]
It's been a long journey,
Madam President.

1086
01:24:05,333 --> 01:24:07,267
I'm afraid
we're just getting started.

1087
01:24:07,333 --> 01:24:09,133
Henry.

1088
01:24:09,200 --> 01:24:11,100
Ethan.

1089
01:24:11,166 --> 01:24:13,100
Our Africa group
is preparing a brief
on Sangala.

1090
01:24:13,166 --> 01:24:15,766
You'll have it
on your desk as soon
as you're done here.

1091
01:24:15,833 --> 01:24:18,734
Good morning.
Good morning.
Congratulations.

1092
01:24:18,833 --> 01:24:21,333
Thank you.
Madam President,
it's an honor.

1093
01:24:21,400 --> 01:24:25,166
Good morning.
Thank you so much.

1094
01:24:26,966 --> 01:24:29,966
You look beautiful,
Madam President.

1095
01:24:30,033 --> 01:24:32,734
Thank you, Samantha.

1096
01:24:32,799 --> 01:24:35,166
Father.
Roger. Samantha.

1097
01:24:35,233 --> 01:24:38,799
Nice to see you on time
for once.
Mm-hmm. [ Chuckles ]

1098
01:24:38,866 --> 01:24:42,100
How are you holding up?
It still doesn't feel
quite real.

1099
01:24:42,166 --> 01:24:43,966
It will soon enough.

1100
01:24:49,600 --> 01:24:52,833
Whitley needed
some encouragement,
but he told my man everything.

1101
01:24:55,600 --> 01:24:57,500
How much
does Roger Taylor know?

1102
01:24:57,567 --> 01:25:01,233
- Nothing you need
to worry about.
- He knows Nichols was involved.

1103
01:25:01,300 --> 01:25:06,799
All he knows is that his
desperate, drug-addicted friend
told him some crazy story.

1104
01:25:06,866 --> 01:25:08,799
He's got no evidence.

1105
01:25:08,866 --> 01:25:12,100
If he finds Nichols,
he could find me.

1106
01:25:12,166 --> 01:25:14,166
Not without evidence.

1107
01:25:17,367 --> 01:25:19,133
Sir,

1108
01:25:19,200 --> 01:25:21,133
Whitley's no longer
a problem.

1109
01:25:21,200 --> 01:25:23,467
We limited the damage.

1110
01:25:23,533 --> 01:25:26,799
But you haven't
eliminated it.

1111
01:25:28,333 --> 01:25:30,799
[ President-elect Taylor ]
Thank you.

1112
01:25:30,866 --> 01:25:33,766
Keep your eye on Taylor.

1113
01:25:36,133 --> 01:25:38,033
How much farther
to the embassy?

1114
01:25:38,100 --> 01:25:40,667
Two more blocks that way.
But we only have
10 minutes.

1115
01:25:40,734 --> 01:25:45,200
As soon as we get there I'm
gonna give you the paperwork.
Give that to Mr. Tramell.

1116
01:25:45,267 --> 01:25:47,734
He's gonna take care
of everything.
Then you're not coming?

1117
01:25:47,799 --> 01:25:49,333
No.
Where's Mr. Benton?

1118
01:25:49,400 --> 01:25:51,033
- He's not coming.
- Why?

1119
01:25:51,100 --> 01:25:53,367
He's dead!

1120
01:25:53,433 --> 01:25:57,933
No! He was supposed
to be behind us!
He said he was coming!

1121
01:25:58,000 --> 01:26:00,766
Willie. Willie!
Willie!

1122
01:26:00,833 --> 01:26:04,100
He lied! Why?
Stop it! Stop it!

1123
01:26:04,166 --> 01:26:07,333
He lied to me? Why?
Mr. Benton
did not lie.

1124
01:26:07,400 --> 01:26:11,367
He made one promise to all
of you boys-- to protect you
and make sure you were safe.

1125
01:26:12,933 --> 01:26:16,333
Mr. Benton died to make sure
that Juma's soldiers
couldn't follow us.

1126
01:26:16,400 --> 01:26:19,300
Mr. Benton died
to make sure you could
get to the embassy.

1127
01:26:19,367 --> 01:26:23,467
Mr. Benton died
to make sure
that you would be safe.

1128
01:26:23,533 --> 01:26:26,066
[ Sobbing ]

1129
01:26:30,734 --> 01:26:32,766
I'm so sorry,

1130
01:26:34,100 --> 01:26:37,400
but we have to go.

1131
01:26:37,467 --> 01:26:39,766
It's what Mr. Benton
would have wanted.

1132
01:26:39,833 --> 01:26:43,533
Okay? You okay?

1133
01:26:43,600 --> 01:26:46,567
Well, then let's go.
Come on. Come on.

1134
01:26:46,634 --> 01:26:49,133
We gotta go.
Right away.

1135
01:26:51,267 --> 01:26:54,333
It's okay. Come on.
Let's go. Let's go.

1136
01:26:59,766 --> 01:27:02,667
Stop. Stop.
Thomas, take the boys.
Hide behind the car. Now.

1137
01:27:02,734 --> 01:27:05,433
Move. Move.
Everybody, now.

1138
01:27:17,600 --> 01:27:19,766
[ Bystanders Screaming ]
[ Machine Gun Fire ]

1139
01:27:48,200 --> 01:27:50,567
Kill the cockroach.

1140
01:27:50,634 --> 01:27:53,000
- Kill the cockroach.
- Put the gun down.

1141
01:27:53,066 --> 01:27:56,300
Kill the cockroach.
I don't want to hurt you.
Just put the gun down.

1142
01:27:56,367 --> 01:27:58,600
Willie, wait!
Willie!

1143
01:27:58,667 --> 01:28:02,367
I know you're scared.
Just put the gun down.
I'm not gonna hurt you.

1144
01:28:03,400 --> 01:28:06,100
Just put the gun down now.

1145
01:28:08,634 --> 01:28:10,267
Willie!

1146
01:28:10,333 --> 01:28:12,766
See those boys?
They're just like you.

1147
01:28:12,833 --> 01:28:16,400
I'm trying to get them out
of the country, somewhere safe
where no one can hurt them.

1148
01:28:16,467 --> 01:28:20,433
You can come with us.
Just put the gun down.

1149
01:28:20,500 --> 01:28:23,833
Come on. Just like me.
Watch. See?

1150
01:28:23,899 --> 01:28:26,899
It's going down.
Like me.

1151
01:28:26,966 --> 01:28:30,267
Come with me.
I promise no one will hurt you.
[ Helicopter Rotors Whirring ]

1152
01:28:30,333 --> 01:28:32,533
No one will hurt you.

1153
01:28:33,467 --> 01:28:35,899
Wait!
[ Thomas ]
Come on, Jack.

1154
01:28:35,966 --> 01:28:39,600
We have to go.
We have to go now!

1155
01:28:39,667 --> 01:28:42,533
Boys! Come with me now!
Come on!

1156
01:28:42,600 --> 01:28:45,533
Let's go!
Everybody hold hands!
Come on!

1157
01:28:45,600 --> 01:28:47,634
[ Panting ]

1158
01:28:47,700 --> 01:28:50,734
[ Shouting, Chattering ]

1159
01:28:53,033 --> 01:28:55,766
I need to speak
to President Taylor.

1160
01:28:55,833 --> 01:28:59,634
As soon as you get to Germany
you will have direct access.

1161
01:28:59,700 --> 01:29:02,667
You really need to go,
Mr. Prime Minister.

1162
01:29:02,734 --> 01:29:05,233
Mrs. Matobo is waiting.

1163
01:29:12,634 --> 01:29:15,000
Keep moving!
Stay right behind me!

1164
01:29:15,066 --> 01:29:17,066
Stay behind me!

1165
01:29:28,966 --> 01:29:30,899
[ Shouts ]

1166
01:29:30,966 --> 01:29:33,667
Everybody hold on
to the person behind you!

1167
01:29:33,734 --> 01:29:35,667
Don't let go!

1168
01:29:35,734 --> 01:29:37,634
Thomas,
keep everyone together!

1169
01:29:37,700 --> 01:29:40,634
[ Shouting Continues ]

1170
01:29:42,200 --> 01:29:44,933
[ Jack ]
Stay together!
Stay together!

1171
01:29:45,000 --> 01:29:47,166
Oh, please take us!

1172
01:29:47,233 --> 01:29:50,200
Sergeant! I need
to see Frank Tramell!
He's expecting me!

1173
01:29:50,267 --> 01:29:53,066
- Who are you?
- Jack Bauer!

1174
01:29:54,833 --> 01:29:57,933
We're almost there!
Just stay with me!

1175
01:29:59,300 --> 01:30:01,866
Everyone together.

1176
01:30:12,966 --> 01:30:16,866
Don't worry, Desmond!
We made it!
We're going to America!

1177
01:30:18,799 --> 01:30:21,667
Tramell!
Listen to me!

1178
01:30:21,734 --> 01:30:25,700
I've got 14 children
seeking political asylum!
All of them are R-1 status!

1179
01:30:25,799 --> 01:30:28,000
One of them
needs urgent medical care!

1180
01:30:28,066 --> 01:30:30,000
Where's Benton?
He's dead!

1181
01:30:30,066 --> 01:30:33,899
Wait! Wait!
I've got their paperwork!

1182
01:30:33,966 --> 01:30:35,933
Show me.

1183
01:30:36,000 --> 01:30:38,200
Keep Desmond up!

1184
01:30:38,267 --> 01:30:40,000
There!

1185
01:30:46,600 --> 01:30:49,267
It's all right.
Stay with me. Come on!

1186
01:31:00,833 --> 01:31:03,899
They appear to be in order.
Good. Then open the gate
and let 'em in!

1187
01:31:03,966 --> 01:31:07,734
There's just one small problem--
They need the legal guardianship
of a U.S. citizen.

1188
01:31:07,799 --> 01:31:10,100
Guardianship?
I already told you--
Benton is dead!

1189
01:31:10,166 --> 01:31:12,133
He died getting
these children here!

1190
01:31:12,200 --> 01:31:14,133
Then don't let him
have died in vain.

1191
01:31:14,200 --> 01:31:18,500
Surrender to the subpoena,
and the ambassador will waive
the issue of guardianship.

1192
01:31:18,567 --> 01:31:22,367
- Tramell, leave me out of this.
- I'm afraid I can't do that.

1193
01:31:22,433 --> 01:31:24,766
We are talking about
innocent children.

1194
01:31:24,833 --> 01:31:26,667
Whatever happens to them
is all on you.

1195
01:31:26,734 --> 01:31:31,267
You would leave these children
out here in the street,
knowing what you do about Juma?

1196
01:31:31,333 --> 01:31:34,300
Damn it, Frank,
they will be used
as cannon fodder...

1197
01:31:34,367 --> 01:31:37,200
or slaughtered
in the soccer stadium
for entertainment!

1198
01:31:37,267 --> 01:31:40,700
I am giving you the chance to
make sure that doesn't happen!

1199
01:31:40,766 --> 01:31:43,200
The choice is yours.

1200
01:31:50,467 --> 01:31:53,766
I don't have a choice,
you son of a bitch.
Open the gate.

1201
01:31:57,066 --> 01:31:59,600
Hold on, boys!
Hold on!

1202
01:31:59,667 --> 01:32:02,133
Desmond, come on!
No, no, no.

1203
01:32:02,200 --> 01:32:04,933
You in first, Bauer.

1204
01:32:05,000 --> 01:32:08,333
It's all right, Willie.
It's all right.
It's all right.

1205
01:32:08,400 --> 01:32:10,333
Right. Take him into custody
right now!

1206
01:32:10,400 --> 01:32:13,000
Let 'em in!
Let them in!

1207
01:32:15,833 --> 01:32:20,500
Let them in!
They're with me!
Let 'em in, damn it!

1208
01:32:32,467 --> 01:32:35,166
No! Those two
are with me too!

1209
01:32:35,233 --> 01:32:37,333
All of them!
All of them!

1210
01:32:37,400 --> 01:32:39,333
[ Grunts ]

1211
01:32:39,400 --> 01:32:42,300
It's all right, Willie.
Just go with them.
Go with the soldiers.

1212
01:32:42,367 --> 01:32:44,367
[ Soldier ]
What about the choppers?

1213
01:32:52,567 --> 01:32:54,799
[ Tramell ]
All right, boys, come on.

1214
01:32:56,533 --> 01:32:58,400
[ Jack ]
It's all right.

1215
01:33:05,000 --> 01:33:07,667
[ Man ]
Raise your right hand
and repeat after me.

1216
01:33:07,734 --> 01:33:10,267
I, Allison Taylor,
do solemnly swear--

1217
01:33:10,333 --> 01:33:13,066
I, Allison Taylor,
do solemnly swear--

1218
01:33:13,133 --> 01:33:16,899
That I will faithfully execute
the office of the president
of the United States--

1219
01:33:16,966 --> 01:33:18,899
That I will
faithfully execute...

1220
01:33:18,966 --> 01:33:21,333
the office of the president
of the United States--

1221
01:33:21,400 --> 01:33:24,866
[ Man ] And will,
to the best of my ability,
preserve, protect and defend...

1222
01:33:24,933 --> 01:33:26,866
the constitution
of the United States--

1223
01:33:26,933 --> 01:33:31,066
And will,
to the best of my ability,
preserve, protect and defend...

1224
01:33:31,133 --> 01:33:33,899
the constitution
of the United States--

1225
01:33:33,966 --> 01:33:36,433
So help me God.
So help me God.

1226
01:33:36,500 --> 01:33:38,267
Congratulations,
Madam President.
Thank you.

1227
01:33:38,333 --> 01:33:40,300
Thank you, Chief Justice.

1228
01:33:50,233 --> 01:33:52,500
Keep going.
Keep going.

1229
01:33:57,333 --> 01:33:59,734
When the founders
of our country...

1230
01:33:59,799 --> 01:34:04,133
boldly declared America's
independence to the world,

1231
01:34:04,200 --> 01:34:07,866
they knew that they derived
their power to govern...

1232
01:34:07,933 --> 01:34:10,667
from three basic
human rights--

1233
01:34:10,734 --> 01:34:15,200
life, liberty
and the pursuit
of happiness.

1234
01:34:15,267 --> 01:34:17,467
Today...

1235
01:34:17,533 --> 01:34:20,367
we rededicate ourselves...

1236
01:34:20,433 --> 01:34:25,033
to the preservation
of those inalienable rights.

1237
01:34:26,033 --> 01:34:27,966
But even as
we carry forth...

1238
01:34:28,033 --> 01:34:31,300
the torch lit
by those great men,

1239
01:34:31,367 --> 01:34:33,833
we need to remember...

1240
01:34:33,899 --> 01:34:38,333
its light doesn't always shine
as brightly as it should.

1241
01:34:39,567 --> 01:34:43,233
It flickers and grows dim...

1242
01:34:43,300 --> 01:34:46,567
because of apathy,
greed...

1243
01:34:48,100 --> 01:34:50,333
and fear.

1244
01:34:52,433 --> 01:34:54,966
De Tocqueville said,

1245
01:34:55,033 --> 01:34:57,467
"In every democracy...

1246
01:34:57,533 --> 01:35:00,833
the people get
the government they deserve."

1247
01:35:02,166 --> 01:35:04,300
Today...

1248
01:35:04,367 --> 01:35:07,166
I am asking
each of you...

1249
01:35:07,233 --> 01:35:09,166
to help me
give you...

1250
01:35:09,233 --> 01:35:13,033
the government
you deserve.

1251
01:35:14,100 --> 01:35:16,833
We all share
the responsibility...

1252
01:35:16,899 --> 01:35:19,799
history has placed
in our hands.

1253
01:35:21,233 --> 01:35:23,533
The future--

1254
01:35:23,600 --> 01:35:26,066
Our future...

1255
01:35:27,133 --> 01:35:29,133
depends on it.

1256
01:35:37,133 --> 01:35:40,100
[ Cheering ]



